question: Which organizations have a public status and are located in cities within the 'United States of America'?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:IN_CITY]->(c:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(country:Country {name: 'United States of America'})
WHERE o.isPublic IS NOT NULL AND o.isPublic = true
RETURN o.name AS organization, c.name AS city
typeql: match $o isa organization, has name $org_name, has is_public $public; $c isa city, has city_name $city_name; $country isa country, has country_name "United States of America"; $l1(located_org: $o, location_city: $c) isa location; $l2(located_city: $c, location_country: $country) isa country_location; $public == true; fetch { "organization": $org_name, "city": $city_name };

question: Which organizations are based in cities that are part of a country with the summary containing 'North America'?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:IN_CITY]->(:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(c:Country)
WHERE c.summary CONTAINS 'North America'
RETURN o.name AS organization, c.name AS country
typeql: match $o isa organization; $loc (located_org: $o, location_city: $city) isa location; $country_loc (located_city: $city, location_country: $c) isa country_location; $c has country_summary $summary; $summary contains "North America"; $c has country_name $country_name; $o has name $org_name; fetch { "organization": $org_name, "country": $country_name };

question: Which people are board members in organizations with more than 1000 employees?
cypher:
MATCH (p:Person)<-[:HAS_BOARD_MEMBER]-(o:Organization)
WHERE o.nbrEmployees > 1000
RETURN p.name AS person, o.name AS organization, o.nbrEmployees AS numEmployees
typeql: match $b (governed_org: $o, board_member: $p) isa board_membership; $o isa organization, has nbr_employees $e, has name $on; $p isa person, has name $pn; $e > 1000; fetch { "person": $pn, "organization": $on, "numEmployees": $e };

question: Who are the CEOs of organizations that have subsidiaries?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_SUBSIDIARY]->(:Organization), (o)-[:HAS_CEO]->(ceo:Person)
RETURN o.name AS organization, ceo.name AS ceo
typeql: match $o isa organization, has name $org_name; $sub_rel(parent_org: $o, subsidiary_org: $sub) isa subsidiary; $ceo_rel(led_org: $o, ceo: $ceo) isa ceo_leadership; $ceo isa person, has name $ceo_name; fetch { "organization": $org_name, "ceo": $ceo_name };

question: List all organizations with the word 'Energy' in their name and their corresponding industry categories.
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_CATEGORY]->(c:IndustryCategory)
WHERE o.name CONTAINS 'Energy'
RETURN o.name AS organization, c.name AS category
typeql: match $o isa organization, has name $org_name; $rel(categorized_org: $o, category: $c) isa categorization; $c isa industry_category, has industry_category_name $cat_name; $org_name contains "Energy"; fetch { "organization": $org_name, "category": $cat_name };

question: List the names and titles of articles mentioning organizations that have been dissolved.
cypher:
MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization)
WHERE o.isDissolved = true
RETURN a.title AS articleTitle, a.summary AS articleSummary
typeql: match $a isa article, has title $title, has article_summary $summary; $rel(mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $o) isa mention; $o isa organization, has is_dissolved true; fetch { "articleTitle": $title, "articleSummary": $summary };

question: Who are the board members of organizations with more than 300 employees?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_BOARD_MEMBER]->(p:Person)
WHERE o.nbrEmployees > 300
RETURN o.name AS organization, p.name AS board_member
typeql: match $o isa organization, has nbr_employees $emp, has name $org_name; $rel (governed_org: $o, board_member: $p) isa board_membership; $p isa person, has name $board_name; $emp > 300; fetch { "organization": $org_name, "board_member": $board_name };

question: Find the organizations that are suppliers to 'New Energy Group' and their number of employees.
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)<-[:HAS_SUPPLIER]-(supplier:Organization {name: 'New Energy Group'})
WHERE supplier.nbrEmployees IS NOT NULL
RETURN supplier.name AS supplier, supplier.nbrEmployees AS numberOfEmployees
typeql: match $supplier isa organization, has name "New Energy Group", has nbr_employees $emp; $rel (supplier_org: $supplier, supplied_org: $o) isa supply; fetch { "supplier": "New Energy Group", "numberOfEmployees": $emp };

question: Which organizations have an investor named 'David Correa'?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)<-[:HAS_INVESTOR]-(p:Person {name: 'David Correa'})
RETURN o.name AS organization
typeql: match $p isa person, has name "David Correa"; $rel (investor: $p, invested_org: $o) isa investment; $o isa organization, has name $org_name; fetch { "organization": $org_name };

question: List the names and summaries of articles that mention organizations with a revenue of at least $1 million.
cypher:
MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization)
WHERE o.revenue >= 1e6
RETURN a.title AS title, a.summary AS summary
typeql: match $a isa article, has title $title, has article_summary $summary; $rel (mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $o) isa mention; $o isa organization, has revenue $rev; $rev >= 1000000.0; fetch { "title": $title, "summary": $summary };

question: Who are the CEOs of organizations that have subsidiaries?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_SUBSIDIARY]->(:Organization), (o)-[:HAS_CEO]->(ceo:Person)
RETURN o.name AS organization, ceo.name AS ceo
typeql: match $o isa organization; $sub (parent_org: $o, subsidiary_org: $s) isa subsidiary; $ceo_rel (led_org: $o, ceo: $ceo) isa ceo_leadership; $o has name $org_name; $ceo has name $ceo_name; fetch { "organization": $org_name, "ceo": $ceo_name };

question: List the cities where organizations with more than 500 employees are based.
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:IN_CITY]->(c:City)
WHERE o.nbrEmployees > 500
RETURN DISTINCT c.name
typeql: match $o isa organization, has nbr_employees $emp; $loc (located_org: $o, location_city: $c) isa location; $c has city_name $city_name; $emp > 500; fetch { "city_name": $city_name };

question: Which organizations have 'Electronic Products Manufacturers' as their industry category?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_CATEGORY]->(c:IndustryCategory {name: 'Electronic Products Manufacturers'})
RETURN o.name AS organization
typeql: match $o isa organization; $cat (categorized_org: $o, category: $c) isa categorization; $c has industry_category_name "Electronic Products Manufacturers"; $o has name $org_name; fetch { "organization": $org_name };

question: What are the names of organizations that have suppliers also mentioned in articles?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_SUPPLIER]->(s:Organization)<-[:MENTIONS]-(a:Article)
RETURN DISTINCT o.name
typeql: match $o isa organization; $sup (supplied_org: $o, supplier_org: $s) isa supply; $men (mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $s) isa mention; $o has name $org_name; fetch { "name": $org_name };

question: Which organizations have a motto and are based in cities in the United States?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:IN_CITY]->(c:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(country:Country {name: 'United States of America'})
WHERE o.motto IS NOT NULL
RETURN o.name AS organization, o.motto AS motto, c.name AS city
typeql: match $o isa organization, has motto $motto; $loc (located_org: $o, location_city: $c) isa location; $cloc (located_city: $c, location_country: $country) isa country_location; $country has country_name "United States of America"; $o has name $org_name; $c has city_name $city_name; fetch { "organization": $org_name, "motto": $motto, "city": $city_name };

question: List the top 5 articles by sentiment that mention organizations based in California.
cypher:
MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization)-[:IN_CITY]->(:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(c:Country {name: 'United States of America'})
WHERE o.summary CONTAINS 'California'
RETURN a.title AS article, a.sentiment AS sentiment
ORDER BY sentiment DESC
LIMIT 5
typeql: match $a isa article, has sentiment $sentiment; $men (mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $o) isa mention; $o has summary $summary; $summary contains "California"; $a has title $title; sort $sentiment desc; limit 5; fetch { "article": $title, "sentiment": $sentiment };

question: Which articles published in 2022 mention organizations with more than 100 employees?
cypher:
MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization)
WHERE a.date.year = 2022 AND o.nbrEmployees > 100
RETURN a.title, a.siteName, a.date, o.name, o.nbrEmployees
typeql: match $a isa article, has date $date, has title $title, has site_name $site; $men (mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $o) isa mention; $o has name $org_name, has nbr_employees $emp; $date >= 2022-01-01T00:00:00; $date < 2023-01-01T00:00:00; $emp > 100; fetch { "title": $title, "siteName": $site, "date": $date, "organization": $org_name, "employees": $emp };

question: Which organizations have a supplier based in a different country?
cypher:
MATCH (o1:Organization)-[:HAS_SUPPLIER]->(o2:Organization),
       (o1)-[:IN_CITY]->(:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(c1:Country),
       (o2)-[:IN_CITY]->(:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(c2:Country)
WHERE c1 <> c2
RETURN o1.name AS Organization, o2.name AS Supplier, c1.name AS OrgCountry, c2.name AS SupplierCountry
typeql: match $o1 isa organization, has name $org_name; $o2 isa organization, has name $supplier_name; $supply_rel (supplied_org: $o1, supplier_org: $o2) isa supply; $loc1 (located_org: $o1, location_city: $city1) isa location; $loc2 (located_org: $o2, location_city: $city2) isa location; $country_loc1 (located_city: $city1, location_country: $c1) isa country_location; $country_loc2 (located_city: $city2, location_country: $c2) isa country_location; $c1 isa country, has country_name $country1_name; $c2 isa country, has country_name $country2_name; not { $c1 is $c2; }; fetch { "organization": $org_name, "supplier": $supplier_name, "org_country": $country1_name, "supplier_country": $country2_name };

question: List articles that mention organizations headquartered in Seattle.
cypher:
MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization)-[:IN_CITY]->(:City {name: 'Seattle'})
RETURN a.title AS article, o.name AS organization
typeql: match $a isa article, has title $title; $o isa organization, has name $org_name; $city isa city, has city_name "Seattle"; $mention_rel (mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $o) isa mention; $loc_rel (located_org: $o, location_city: $city) isa location; fetch { "article": $title, "organization": $org_name };

question: Which organizations are based in cities with a population of more than one million people according to city summaries?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:IN_CITY]->(c:City)
WHERE c.summary CONTAINS 'population of more than one million'
RETURN o.name AS organization, c.name AS city
typeql: match $o isa organization; $c isa city; $loc_rel (located_org: $o, location_city: $c) isa location; $c has city_summary $summary; $summary like ".*population of more than one million.*"; $o has name $org_name; $c has city_name $city_name; fetch { "organization": $org_name, "city": $city_name };

question: Who are the board members of New Energy Group?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization {name: "New Energy Group"})-[:HAS_BOARD_MEMBER]->(p:Person)
RETURN p.name AS boardMember
typeql: match $o isa organization, has name "New Energy Group"; $p isa person; $board_rel (governed_org: $o, board_member: $p) isa board_membership; $p has name $board_member; fetch { "boardMember": $board_member };

question: List the countries where the top 5 organizations by revenue are based.
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:IN_CITY]->(:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(c:Country)
WITH o, c
ORDER BY o.revenue DESC
LIMIT 5
RETURN DISTINCT c.name AS country
typeql: match $o isa organization, has revenue $r; $loc(located_org: $o, location_city: $city) isa location; $country_loc(located_city: $city, location_country: $c) isa country_location; $c has country_name $name; sort $r desc; limit 5; fetch { "country": $name };

question: What are the top 3 most recent articles mentioning Deja vu Security?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization {name: 'Deja vu Security'})<-[:MENTIONS]-(a:Article)
RETURN a.title, a.date, a.summary
ORDER BY a.date DESC
LIMIT 3
typeql: match $o isa organization, has name "Deja vu Security"; $m(mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $o) isa mention; $a has title $title, has date $date, has article_summary $summary; sort $date desc; limit 3; fetch { "title": $title, "date": $date, "summary": $summary };

question: Who are the children of Julie Spellman Sweet?
cypher:
MATCH (p:Person {name: "Julie Spellman Sweet"})-[:HAS_CHILD]->(child:Person)
RETURN child.name AS name
typeql: match $p isa person, has name "Julie Spellman Sweet"; $pc(parent: $p, child: $child) isa parent_child; $child has name $name; fetch { "name": $name };

question: List the first 3 subsidiaries of Accenture.
cypher:
MATCH (accenture:Organization {name: 'Accenture'})-[:HAS_SUBSIDIARY]->(subsidiary:Organization)
RETURN subsidiary.name
LIMIT 3
typeql: match $accenture isa organization, has name "Accenture"; $sub(parent_org: $accenture, subsidiary_org: $subsidiary) isa subsidiary; $subsidiary has name $name; limit 3; fetch { "name": $name };

question: What are the first 3 companies that are competitors of New Energy Group?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization {name: "New Energy Group"})-[:HAS_COMPETITOR]->(competitor:Organization)
RETURN competitor.name
LIMIT 3
typeql: match $o isa organization, has name "New Energy Group"; $comp(competitor: $o, competitor: $competitor) isa competition; $competitor has name $name; limit 3; fetch { "name": $name };

question: Which organizations have a sentiment score higher than 0.8 in their latest article?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)<-[:MENTIONS]-(a:Article)
WHERE a.sentiment > 0.8
WITH o, max(a.date) AS latestDate
MATCH (o)<-[:MENTIONS]-(article:Article {date: latestDate})
RETURN o.name AS organization, article.title AS latestArticle, article.sentiment AS sentiment
typeql: match $o isa organization; $m(mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $o) isa mention; $a has sentiment $s, has date $date; $s > 0.8; fetch { "organization": $o.name, "sentiment": $s, "date": $date };

question: List the top 5 suppliers of Accenture.
cypher:
MATCH (a:Organization {name: 'Accenture'})<-[:HAS_SUPPLIER]-(s:Organization)
RETURN s.name AS supplier, s.summary AS summary
ORDER BY s.revenue DESC
LIMIT 5
typeql: match $a isa organization, has name "Accenture"; $sup(supplier_org: $s, supplied_org: $a) isa supply; $s has name $name, has summary $summary, has revenue $r; sort $r desc; limit 5; fetch { "supplier": $name, "summary": $summary };

question: What are the names of the first 3 organizations with a motto?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)
WHERE o.motto IS NOT NULL
RETURN o.name
LIMIT 3
typeql: match $o isa organization, has motto $motto, has name $name; limit 3; fetch { "name": $name };

question: Which organizations have more than 500 employees and are located in Seattle?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:IN_CITY]->(c:City {name: 'Seattle'})
WHERE o.nbrEmployees > 500
RETURN o.name AS organization, o.nbrEmployees AS numberOfEmployees
typeql: match $o isa organization, has nbr_employees $emp, has name $name; $loc(located_org: $o, location_city: $c) isa location; $c has city_name "Seattle"; $emp > 500; fetch { "organization": $name, "numberOfEmployees": $emp };

question: Name 3 organizations mentioned in articles written by David Correa.
cypher:
MATCH (a:Article {author: 'David Correa'})-[:HAS_CHUNK]->(c:Chunk), 
      (a)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization)
RETURN o.name
LIMIT 3
typeql: match $a isa article, has author "David Correa"; $m(mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $o) isa mention; $o has name $name; limit 3; fetch { "name": $name };

question: Which articles about 'New Energy Group' were published after 2020-01-01?
cypher:
MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization {name: 'New Energy Group'})
WHERE a.date > date('2020-01-01')
RETURN a.title, a.date, a.siteName, a.summary
typeql: match $a isa article, has title $t, has date $d, has site_name $sn, has article_summary $as; $m (mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $o) isa mention; $o isa organization, has name "New Energy Group"; $d > 2020-01-01T00:00:00; fetch { "title": $t, "date": $d, "site_name": $sn, "summary": $as };

question: What are the names of the organizations that have 'Icon Integration' as a subsidiary?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_SUBSIDIARY]->(s:Organization {name: 'Icon Integration'})
RETURN o.name
typeql: match $o isa organization, has name $on; $sub (parent_org: $o, subsidiary_org: $s) isa subsidiary; $s isa organization, has name "Icon Integration"; fetch { "name": $on };

question: Which organizations have more than 50 employees and are in the 'Software' industry?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_CATEGORY]->(c:IndustryCategory {name: 'Software'})
WHERE o.nbrEmployees > 50
RETURN o.name AS organization, o.nbrEmployees AS numberOfEmployees
typeql: match $o isa organization, has name $on, has nbr_employees $ne; $cat (categorized_org: $o, category: $c) isa categorization; $c isa industry_category, has industry_category_name "Software"; $ne > 50; fetch { "organization": $on, "number_of_employees": $ne };

question: Which cities host organizations that are public and have a CEO named 'Julie Spellman Sweet'?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_CEO]->(p:Person {name: 'Julie Spellman Sweet'}),
      (o)-[:IN_CITY]->(c:City)
WHERE o.isPublic IS NOT NULL AND o.isPublic = true
RETURN DISTINCT c.name
typeql: match $o isa organization, has is_public true; $ceo isa person, has name "Julie Spellman Sweet"; $c isa city, has city_name $name; (led_org: $o, ceo: $ceo) isa ceo_leadership; (located_org: $o, location_city: $c) isa location; fetch { "name": $name };

question: List the first 3 articles that mention any organization with more than 1000 employees and are written after 2021-01-01.
cypher:
MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization)
WHERE o.nbrEmployees > 1000 AND a.date > date("2021-01-01")
RETURN a.title, a.date, o.name
LIMIT 3
typeql: match $a isa article, has title $title, has date $date; $o isa organization, has name $org_name, has nbr_employees $emp; (mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $o) isa mention; $emp > 1000; $date > 2021-01-01T00:00:00; sort $date asc; limit 3; fetch { "title": $title, "date": $date, "name": $org_name };

question: Who are the children of 'Julie Spellman Sweet' listed as 'Person' nodes?
cypher:
MATCH (p:Person {name: 'Julie Spellman Sweet'})-[:HAS_CHILD]->(child:Person)
RETURN child.name AS childName
typeql: match $p isa person, has name "Julie Spellman Sweet"; $child isa person, has name $child_name; (parent: $p, child: $child) isa parent_child; fetch { "childName": $child_name };

question: Find the top 5 parent persons of CEOs of organizations with revenues exceeding 100 million.
cypher:
MATCH (p:Person)<-[:HAS_PARENT]-(ceo:Person)<-[:HAS_CEO]-(o:Organization)
WHERE o.revenue > 1E8
RETURN p.name AS parent_name, ceo.name AS ceo_name, o.name AS org_name, o.revenue AS revenue
ORDER BY o.revenue DESC
LIMIT 5
typeql: match $p isa person, has name $parent_name; $ceo isa person, has name $ceo_name; $o isa organization, has name $org_name, has revenue $revenue; (parent: $p, child: $ceo) isa parent_child; (led_org: $o, ceo: $ceo) isa ceo_leadership; $revenue > 100000000; sort $revenue desc; limit 5; fetch { "parent_name": $parent_name, "ceo_name": $ceo_name, "org_name": $org_name, "revenue": $revenue };

question: List the first 3 articles that have chunks containing the text 'consumer behavior'.
cypher:
MATCH (a:Article)-[:HAS_CHUNK]->(c:Chunk)
WHERE c.text CONTAINS 'consumer behavior'
RETURN a.title, a.siteName, a.date
LIMIT 3
typeql: match $a isa article, has title $title, has site_name $site_name, has date $date; $c isa chunk, has text $text; (parent_article: $a, child_chunk: $c) isa chunk_relation; $text contains "consumer behavior"; limit 3; fetch { "title": $title, "siteName": $site_name, "date": $date };

question: What are the names of organizations with more than 500 employees and have been mentioned in articles with high sentiment scores?
typeql: match $o isa organization, has name $org_name, has nbr_employees $emp; $a isa article, has sentiment $sentiment; (mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $o) isa mention; $emp > 500; $sentiment > 0.8; fetch { "name": $org_name };

question: Which 3 organizations are suppliers to 'New Energy Group' and are based in 'United States of America'?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization {name: 'New Energy Group'})<-[:HAS_SUPPLIER]-(supplier:Organization)-[:IN_CITY]->(:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(c:Country {name: 'United States of America'})
RETURN supplier.name
LIMIT 3
typeql: match $neg isa organization, has name "New Energy Group"; $supplier isa organization, has name $supplier_name; $city isa city; $country isa country, has country_name "United States of America"; (supplier_org: $supplier, supplied_org: $neg) isa supply; (located_org: $supplier, location_city: $city) isa location; (location_country: $country, located_city: $city) isa country_location; limit 3; fetch { "name": $supplier_name };

question: List the top 3 CEOs of organizations that are subsidiaries of 'Accenture'.
cypher:
MATCH (accenture:Organization {name: 'Accenture'})-[:HAS_SUBSIDIARY*]->(sub:Organization)
WHERE EXISTS {(sub)-[:HAS_CEO]->(:Person)}
WITH sub, sub.name AS subName
MATCH (sub)-[:HAS_CEO]->(ceo:Person)
RETURN ceo.name AS ceoName, subName
ORDER BY ceoName
LIMIT 3

question: Identify the first 3 organizations that have the same investor and are competitors.
cypher:
MATCH (o1:Organization)-[:HAS_INVESTOR]->(investor)<-[:HAS_INVESTOR]-(o2:Organization)
WHERE (o1)-[:HAS_COMPETITOR]->(o2)
RETURN o1.name AS Org1, o2.name AS Org2, investor.name AS CommonInvestor
LIMIT 3

question: Which 3 organizations have the most subsidiaries within the same country?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_SUBSIDIARY]->(sub:Organization),
      (o)-[:IN_CITY]->(:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(c:Country),
      (sub)-[:IN_CITY]->(:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(c)
WITH o, count(sub) AS numSubs
ORDER BY numSubs DESC
LIMIT 3
RETURN o.name AS organization, numSubs AS numberOfSubsidiaries

cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)-[:IN_CITY]->(:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(c:Country {name: 'United States of America'}) WHERE o.nbrEmployees > 5000 RETURN o.name AS organization LIMIT 10

question: List the top 3 organizations that have a CEO and are mentioned in the most articles.
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)<-[:MENTIONS]-(a:Article) WHERE EXISTS {(o)-[:HAS_CEO]->(:Person)} WITH o, count(a) AS mentions ORDER BY mentions DESC LIMIT 3 RETURN o.name AS organization, mentions

question: Who are the first 3 children of CEOs of organizations with more than 500 million in revenue?
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_CEO]->(ceo:Person) WHERE o.revenue > 5e8 WITH ceo MATCH (ceo)-[:HAS_CHILD]->(child:Person) RETURN child.name AS child_name LIMIT 3

question: List the first 3 organizations that have a motto and are public.
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization) WHERE o.motto IS NOT NULL AND o.isPublic = true RETURN o.name AS organization, o.motto AS motto LIMIT 3
typeql: match $o isa organization, has motto $m, has is_public true, has name $n; limit 3; fetch { "organization": $n, "motto": $m };

question: Which organizations have investors named 'Julie Spellman Sweet'?
cypher: MATCH (p:Person {name: 'Julie Spellman Sweet'})-[:HAS_INVESTOR]->(o:Organization) RETURN o.name AS organization

question: Find the first 3 organizations that have been mentioned in articles related to 'consumer behavior'.
cypher: MATCH (a:Article)-[:HAS_CHUNK]->(c:Chunk) WHERE c.text CONTAINS 'consumer behavior' WITH a MATCH (a)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization) RETURN DISTINCT o.name AS organization LIMIT 3

question: Which organizations are based in 'Seattle' and have a revenue less than 1 billion?
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)-[:IN_CITY]->(c:City {name: 'Seattle'}) WHERE o.revenue < 1e9 RETURN o.name AS organization, o.revenue AS revenue

question: List the first 3 organizations that have a dissolved status and are mentioned by articles authored by 'David Correa'.
cypher: MATCH (a:Article {author: 'David Correa'})-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization {isDissolved: true}) RETURN o.name AS organization LIMIT 3

question: Identify the top 3 organizations that have a public status and are in the 'Healthcare' industry category.
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_CATEGORY]->(c:IndustryCategory {name: 'Healthcare'}) WHERE o.isPublic = true RETURN o.name AS organization ORDER BY o.revenue DESC LIMIT 3

question: Who are the first 3 CEOs of organizations that have been mentioned in more than 5 articles?
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)<-[:MENTIONS]-(a:Article) WITH o, count(a) AS mentionCount WHERE mentionCount > 5 MATCH (o)-[:HAS_CEO]->(ceo:Person) RETURN ceo.name AS ceo LIMIT 3

question: List the first 3 articles that mention organizations with CEOs named 'Julie Spellman Sweet'.
cypher: MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization)-[:HAS_CEO]->(p:Person {name: 'Julie Spellman Sweet'}) RETURN a.title AS article_title LIMIT 3

question: Which organizations based in 'United States of America' have a CEO named 'Julie Spellman Sweet'?
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)-[:IN_CITY]->(:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(c:Country {name: 'United States of America'}) MATCH (o)-[:HAS_CEO]->(p:Person {name: 'Julie Spellman Sweet'}) RETURN o.name AS organization

question: Find the first 3 organizations that have a supplier named 'Icon Integration'.
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_SUPPLIER]->(s:Organization {name: 'Icon Integration'}) RETURN o.name AS organization LIMIT 3

question: Identify the first 3 articles where the organizations mentioned have more than 50 employees.
cypher: MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization) WHERE o.nbrEmployees > 50 WITH a, count(o) AS orgCount WHERE orgCount > 1 RETURN a.title AS article_title LIMIT 3

question: Who are the first 3 board members of organizations based in 'Italy'?
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)-[:IN_CITY]->(:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(c:Country {name: 'Italy'}) MATCH (o)-[:HAS_BOARD_MEMBER]->(p:Person) RETURN p.name AS board_member LIMIT 3

question: List the top 3 organizations that have been mentioned in articles with negative sentiment.
cypher: MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization) WHERE a.sentiment < 0.3 WITH o, count(a) AS mentions ORDER BY mentions DESC LIMIT 3 RETURN o.name AS organization, mentions

question: Which organizations have more than 1000 employees and are in the 'Finance' industry category?
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_CATEGORY]->(c:IndustryCategory {name: 'Finance'}) WHERE o.nbrEmployees > 1000 RETURN o.name AS organization

question: List the first 3 organizations with the highest number of employees that are private.
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization) WHERE o.isPublic = false AND o.nbrEmployees IS NOT NULL RETURN o.name AS organization, o.nbrEmployees AS employees ORDER BY o.nbrEmployees DESC LIMIT 3

question: Which organizations have CEOs named 'Julie Spellman Sweet' and are in the 'Technology' industry?
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_CEO]->(p:Person {name: 'Julie Spellman Sweet'}) WHERE EXISTS {(o)-[:HAS_CATEGORY]->(:IndustryCategory {name: 'Technology'})} RETURN o.name AS organization

question: Find the first 3 organizations that have been mentioned in articles with a date after 2023-01-01.
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)<-[:MENTIONS]-(a:Article) WHERE a.date > datetime('2023-01-01') RETURN o.name LIMIT 3
typeql: match $o isa organization, has name $n; $a isa article, has date $d; (mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $o) isa mention; $d > 2023-01-01T00:00:00; limit 3; fetch { "name": $n };

question: Identify the top 3 cities with the most organizations in the 'Technology' industry.
cypher: MATCH (c:City)<-[:LOCATED_IN]-(o:Organization)-[:IN_INDUSTRY]->(i:IndustryCategory {name: 'Technology'}) RETURN c.name, COUNT(o) AS orgCount ORDER BY orgCount DESC LIMIT 3
typeql: match $c isa city, has city_name $cn; $o isa organization; $i isa industry_category, has industry_category_name "Technology"; (located_org: $o, location_city: $c) isa location; (categorized_org: $o, category: $i) isa categorization; reduce $count = count($o), group($cn); sort $count desc; limit 3;

question: Who are the first 3 competitors of organizations named 'Accenture'?
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization {name: 'Accenture'})-[:COMPETITOR_OF]->(c:Organization) RETURN c.name LIMIT 3
typeql: match $o isa organization, has name "Accenture"; $c isa organization, has name $cn; (competitor: $o, competitor: $c) isa competition; $o != $c; limit 3; fetch { "name": $cn };

question: List the 3 most recent articles mentioning any organization in the 'Finance' industry.
cypher: MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization)-[:IN_INDUSTRY]->(i:IndustryCategory {name: 'Finance'}) RETURN a.title, a.date ORDER BY a.date DESC LIMIT 3
typeql: match $a isa article, has title $t, has date $d; $o isa organization; $i isa industry_category, has industry_category_name "Finance"; (mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $o) isa mention; (categorized_org: $o, category: $i) isa categorization; sort $d desc; limit 3; fetch { "title": $t, "date": $d };

question: Which organizations based in 'Seattle' have a CEO named 'Julie Spellman Sweet'?
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)-[:LOCATED_IN]->(c:City {name: 'Seattle'}), (o)-[:HAS_CEO]->(p:Person {name: 'Julie Spellman Sweet'}) RETURN o.name
typeql: match $o isa organization, has name $n; $c isa city, has city_name "Seattle"; $p isa person, has name "Julie Spellman Sweet"; (located_org: $o, location_city: $c) isa location; (led_org: $o, ceo: $p) isa ceo_leadership; fetch { "name": $n };

question: Identify the first 3 organizations that have a CEO and are mentioned in articles with negative sentiment (< 0.3).
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)<-[:CEO_OF]-(p:Person), (o)<-[:MENTIONS]-(a:Article) WHERE a.sentiment < 0.3 RETURN o.name LIMIT 3

question: Who are the first 3 investors in organizations that have a revenue greater than 500 million?
cypher: MATCH (i:Investor)-[:INVESTED_IN]->(o:Organization) WHERE o.revenue > 500000000 RETURN i.name LIMIT 3

question: Find the first 3 articles that mention organizations in the 'Healthcare' industry.
cypher: MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization)-[:IN_INDUSTRY]->(ind:Industry {name: 'Healthcare'}) RETURN a.title LIMIT 3

question: Identify the top 3 organizations that have a public status and are in cities within the 'Germany' country.
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)-[:IN_CITY]->(c:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(co:Country {name: 'Germany'}) WHERE o.is_public = true RETURN o ORDER BY o.name LIMIT 3
typeql: match $o isa organization, has is_public true, has name $n; $c isa city; $co isa country, has country_name "Germany"; (located_org: $o, location_city: $c) isa location; (located_city: $c, location_country: $co) isa country_location; sort $n asc; limit 3; fetch { "name": $n };

question: List the first 3 organizations with the most board members.
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)<-[:MEMBER_OF]-(p:Person) RETURN o, count(p) as board_count ORDER BY board_count DESC LIMIT 3
typeql: match $o isa organization, has name $org_name; (governed_org: $o, board_member: $p) isa board_membership; reduce $board_count = count($p), $name = first($org_name) group $o; sort $board_count desc; limit 3; fetch { "organization": $name, "board_count": $board_count };

question: Which organizations have a CEO named 'Julie Spellman Sweet' and are public?
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)<-[:CEO_OF]-(p:Person {name: 'Julie Spellman Sweet'}) WHERE o.is_public = true RETURN o
typeql: match $o isa organization, has is_public true, has name $org_name; $p isa person, has name "Julie Spellman Sweet"; (led_org: $o, ceo: $p) isa ceo_leadership; fetch { "organization": $org_name };

question: Find the first 3 articles mentioning organizations with a CEO.
cypher: MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization)<-[:CEO_OF]-(p:Person) RETURN DISTINCT a LIMIT 3
typeql: match $a isa article, has title $t; $o isa organization; $p isa person; (mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $o) isa mention; (led_org: $o, ceo: $p) isa ceo_leadership; limit 3; fetch { "title": $t };

question: Identify the top 3 organizations that have been dissolved and are in the 'Technology' industry.
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)-[:IN_INDUSTRY]->(i:Industry {name: 'Technology'}) WHERE o.is_dissolved = true RETURN o ORDER BY o.name LIMIT 3
typeql: match $o isa organization, has is_dissolved true, has name $n; $i isa industry_category, has industry_category_name "Technology"; (categorized_org: $o, category: $i) isa categorization; sort $n asc; limit 3; fetch { "name": $n };

question: Who are the first 3 CEOs of organizations that have subsidiaries?
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_SUBSIDIARY]->(s:Organization), (o)<-[:CEO_OF]-(p:Person) RETURN p.name LIMIT 3
typeql: match $o isa organization; $s isa organization; (parent_org: $o, subsidiary_org: $s) isa subsidiary; $p isa person, has name $n; (ceo: $p, led_org: $o) isa ceo_leadership; limit 3; fetch { "name": $n };

question: List the first 3 articles mentioning organizations with more than 10000 employees.
cypher: MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization) WHERE o.nbrEmployees > 10000 RETURN a.title LIMIT 3
typeql: match $a isa article, has title $t; $o isa organization, has nbr_employees $e; $e > 10000; (mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $o) isa mention; limit 3; fetch { "title": $t };

question: Which organizations have a revenue above 1 billion and are in the 'Finance' industry?
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)-[:IN_CATEGORY]->(c:IndustryCategory {name: 'Finance'}) WHERE o.revenue > 1000000000 RETURN o.name
typeql: match $o isa organization, has name $n, has revenue $r; $r > 1000000000.0; $c isa industry_category, has industry_category_name "Finance"; (categorized_org: $o, category: $c) isa categorization; fetch { "name": $n };

question: Find the first 3 organizations that have a CEO named 'Julie Spellman Sweet' and are mentioned in articles.
cypher: MATCH (p:Person {name: 'Julie Spellman Sweet'})-[:CEO_OF]->(o:Organization)<-[:MENTIONS]-(a:Article) RETURN DISTINCT o.name LIMIT 3
typeql: match $p isa person, has name "Julie Spellman Sweet"; $o isa organization, has name $n; (ceo: $p, led_org: $o) isa ceo_leadership; $a isa article; (mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $o) isa mention; limit 3; fetch { "name": $n };

question: Identify the top 3 organizations that have a CEO and are based in 'United States of America'.
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)-[:LOCATED_IN]->(c:Country {name: 'United States of America'}), (o)<-[:CEO_OF]-(p:Person) RETURN o.name LIMIT 3
typeql: match $o isa organization, has name $n; $p isa person; (ceo: $p, led_org: $o) isa ceo_leadership; $city isa city; (located_org: $o, location_city: $city) isa location; $country isa country, has country_name "United States of America"; (located_city: $city, location_country: $country) isa country_location; limit 3; fetch { "name": $n };

question: Identify the top 3 organizations that have a public status and are based in 'Italy'.
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:IN_CITY]->(:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(c:Country {name: 'Italy'})
WHERE o.isPublic IS NOT NULL AND o.isPublic = true
RETURN o.name AS organization, o.summary AS summary
ORDER BY o.revenue DESC
LIMIT 3

question: List the first 3 organizations with the most board members.
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_BOARD_MEMBER]->(p:Person)
WITH o, count(p) AS boardMemberCount
ORDER BY boardMemberCount DESC
LIMIT 3
RETURN o.name AS organization, boardMemberCount

question: Which organizations have a CEO named 'Julie Spellman Sweet' and are based in 'Italy'?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_CEO]->(p:Person {name: 'Julie Spellman Sweet'})
WHERE (o)-[:IN_CITY]->(:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(:Country {name: 'Italy'})
RETURN o

question: Find the first 3 articles mentioning organizations with a CEO named 'Julie Spellman Sweet' and a revenue above 500 million.
cypher:
MATCH (article:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(org:Organization)
WHERE org.revenue > 5e8 AND (org)-[:HAS_CEO]->(:Person {name: 'Julie Spellman Sweet'})
RETURN article.title, article.summary, article.date
LIMIT 3

question: Identify the top 3 organizations that have been dissolved and are mentioned in high sentiment articles.
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:MENTIONS]-(a:Article)
WHERE o.isDissolved = true
WITH o, avg(a.sentiment) as avgSentiment
ORDER BY avgSentiment DESC
LIMIT 3
RETURN o.name as organization, avgSentiment as avgArticleSentiment

question: Who are the first 3 CEOs of organizations that have subsidiaries and a revenue above 1 billion?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_CEO]->(ceo:Person)
WHERE o.revenue > 1e9 AND EXISTS {(o)-[:HAS_SUBSIDIARY]->(:Organization)}
RETURN ceo.name AS ceoName, o.name AS orgName
LIMIT 3

question: List the first 3 articles mentioning organizations with more than 500 employees and a low sentiment score.
cypher:
MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization)
WHERE o.nbrEmployees > 500 AND a.sentiment < 0.5
RETURN a.title, a.sentiment, o.name
LIMIT 3

question: Which organizations have a revenue above 1 billion and are in the 'Technology' industry?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_CATEGORY]->(c:IndustryCategory {name: 'Technology'})
WHERE o.revenue > 1e9
RETURN o.name AS organization, o.revenue AS revenue

question: Find the first 3 organizations that have a CEO named 'Julie Spellman Sweet' and are based in 'Seattle'.
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_CEO]->(p:Person {name: 'Julie Spellman Sweet'})
WHERE (o)-[:IN_CITY]->(:City {name: 'Seattle'})
RETURN o
LIMIT 3

question: Identify the top 3 organizations that have a CEO and are based in 'New York City'.
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_CEO]->(:Person)
MATCH (o)-[:IN_CITY]->(:City {name: 'New York City'})
RETURN o.name AS organization, o.summary AS summary
ORDER BY o.revenue DESC
LIMIT 3

question: Who are the first 3 board members of organizations with revenues less than 5000000?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_BOARD_MEMBER]->(p:Person)
WHERE o.revenue < 5000000
RETURN p.name
LIMIT 3
typeql: match $o isa organization, has revenue $r; $r < 5000000.0; (governed_org: $o, board_member: $p) isa board_membership; $p has name $n; limit 3; fetch { "name": $n };

question: List the first 3 organizations that have been mentioned in articles with a sentiment score above 0.9.
cypher:
MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization)
WHERE a.sentiment > 0.9
RETURN o.name
LIMIT 3
typeql: match $a isa article, has sentiment $s; $s > 0.9; (mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $o) isa mention; $o has name $n; limit 3; fetch { "name": $n };

question: Which organizations have a CEO named 'Julie Spellman Sweet' and have subsidiaries named 'Icon Integration'?
typeql: match $o isa organization, has name $org_name, has summary $org_summary; $ceo isa person, has name "Julie Spellman Sweet"; $sub isa organization, has name "Icon Integration"; (led_org: $o, ceo: $ceo) isa ceo_leadership; (parent_org: $o, subsidiary_org: $sub) isa subsidiary; fetch { "name": $org_name, "summary": $org_summary };

question: Find the first 3 organizations based in 'Seattle' that have a public status and are not dissolved.
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:IN_CITY]->(:City {name: 'Seattle'})
WHERE o.isPublic = true AND (o.isDissolved = false OR o.isDissolved IS NULL)
RETURN o.name, o.summary
LIMIT 3
typeql: match $o isa organization, has is_public true, has is_dissolved false, has name $n, has summary $s; $c isa city, has city_name "Seattle"; (located_org: $o, location_city: $c) isa location; limit 3; fetch { "name": $n, "summary": $s };

question: Identify the first 3 organizations that have a subsidiary and a CEO named 'Julie Spellman Sweet'.
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_SUBSIDIARY]->(:Organization)
MATCH (o)-[:HAS_CEO]->(ceo:Person {name: 'Julie Spellman Sweet'})
RETURN o.name AS organization
LIMIT 3
typeql: match $o isa organization, has name $org_name; $ceo isa person, has name "Julie Spellman Sweet"; $sub isa organization; (led_org: $o, ceo: $ceo) isa ceo_leadership; (parent_org: $o, subsidiary_org: $sub) isa subsidiary; limit 3; fetch { "organization": $org_name };

question: Who are the first 3 investors in organizations with less than 50 employees?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)<-[:HAS_INVESTOR]-(investor)
WHERE o.nbrEmployees < 50
WITH investor, o
ORDER BY o.nbrEmployees
RETURN DISTINCT investor.name AS investor, o.name AS company
LIMIT 3

question: List the top 3 organizations that have a CEO and have been mentioned in the most recent articles.
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_CEO]->(:Person)
MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(o)
WITH o, count(a) AS mentionCount, max(a.date) AS latestMentionDate
ORDER BY latestMentionDate DESC, mentionCount DESC
RETURN o.name AS organization, latestMentionDate, mentionCount
LIMIT 3

question: Which organizations based in 'United States of America' have a revenue less than 10 million?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:IN_CITY]->(:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(c:Country {name: 'United States of America'})
WHERE o.revenue < 10000000
RETURN o.name AS organization, o.revenue AS revenue

question: Find the first 3 organizations that have CEOs named 'Julie Spellman Sweet' and are mentioned in articles with a sentiment score above 0.5.
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_CEO]->(p:Person {name: 'Julie Spellman Sweet'})
WHERE EXISTS {
  (o)<-[:MENTIONS]-(a:Article)
  WHERE a.sentiment > 0.5
}
RETURN o
LIMIT 3

question: Identify the first 3 organizations that have the same investor and are based in 'Italy'.
cypher:
MATCH (o1:Organization)-[:HAS_INVESTOR]->(investor)<-[:HAS_INVESTOR]-(o2:Organization)
WHERE o1 <> o2 AND o1.id < o2.id
  AND (o1)-[:IN_CITY]->(:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(:Country {name: 'Italy'})
  AND (o2)-[:IN_CITY]->(:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(:Country {name: 'Italy'})
RETURN o1.name AS org1, o2.name AS org2, investor.name AS investor
LIMIT 3

question: Find the names of all companies that are suppliers to 'Apple Inc.'.
cypher: MATCH (s:Company)-[:SUPPLIES]->(c:Company {name: 'Apple Inc.'}) RETURN s.name
typeql: match $c isa organization, has name "Apple Inc."; (supplier_org: $s, supplied_org: $c) isa supply; $s has name $n; fetch { "name": $n };

question: List all companies that are both public and have more than 10000 employees.
cypher: MATCH (c:Company) WHERE c.isPublic = true AND c.nbrEmployees > 10000 RETURN c.name
typeql: match $c isa organization, has is_public true, has nbr_employees $e, has name $n; $e > 10000; fetch { "name": $n };

question: Find all articles that mention companies in the 'Technology' industry category.
cypher: MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(c:Company)-[:HAS_CATEGORY]->(cat:IndustryCategory {name: 'Technology'}) RETURN DISTINCT a.title
typeql: match $cat isa industry_category, has industry_category_name "Technology"; (categorized_org: $c, category: $cat) isa categorization; (mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $c) isa mention; $a has title $t; fetch { "title": $t };

question: List the CEOs of companies headquartered in 'New York'.
cypher: MATCH (p:Person)-[:CEO_OF]->(c:Company)-[:LOCATED_IN]->(city:City {name: 'New York'}) RETURN p.name, c.name
typeql: match $city isa city, has city_name "New York"; (located_org: $c, location_city: $city) isa location; (ceo: $p, led_org: $c) isa ceo_leadership; $p has name $pn; $c has name $cn; fetch { "person_name": $pn, "company_name": $cn };

question: Find all subsidiaries of 'Alphabet Inc.' and their locations.
cypher: MATCH (parent:Company {name: 'Alphabet Inc.'})-[:HAS_SUBSIDIARY]->(sub:Company)-[:LOCATED_IN]->(city:City) RETURN sub.name, city.name
typeql: match $parent isa organization, has name "Alphabet Inc."; (parent_org: $parent, subsidiary_org: $sub) isa subsidiary; (located_org: $sub, location_city: $city) isa location; $sub has name $sn; $city has city_name $cn; fetch { "subsidiary_name": $sn, "city_name": $cn };

question: Which companies have board members who are also CEOs of other companies?
cypher: MATCH (p:Person)-[:BOARD_MEMBER_OF]->(c1:Company), (p)-[:CEO_OF]->(c2:Company) WHERE c1 <> c2 RETURN DISTINCT p.name, c1.name AS board_company, c2.name AS ceo_company
typeql: match $p isa person, has name $pn; (board_member: $p, governed_org: $c1) isa board_membership; (ceo: $p, led_org: $c2) isa ceo_leadership; $c1 has name $bn; $c2 has name $cn; not { $c1 is $c2; }; fetch { "person_name": $pn, "board_company": $bn, "ceo_company": $cn };

question: Find the average revenue of public companies by country.
cypher: MATCH (c:Company)-[:LOCATED_IN]->(city:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(country:Country) WHERE c.isPublic = true RETURN country.name, AVG(c.revenue) AS avg_revenue
typeql: match $c isa organization, has is_public true, has revenue $r; (located_org: $c, location_city: $city) isa location; (located_city: $city, location_country: $country) isa country_location; $country has country_name $cn; reduce $avg_revenue = mean($r);

question: List all companies that compete with 'Microsoft Corporation'.
cypher: MATCH (c:Company)-[:COMPETES_WITH]-(target:Company {name: 'Microsoft Corporation'}) RETURN c.name
typeql: match $target isa organization, has name "Microsoft Corporation"; (competitor: $c, competitor: $target) isa competition; $c has name $n; not { $c is $target; }; fetch { "name": $n };

question: Find articles with negative sentiment about dissolved companies.
cypher: MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(c:Company) WHERE a.sentiment < 0 AND c.isDissolved = true RETURN a.title, c.name
typeql: match $a isa article, has sentiment $s, has title $t; $s < 0; (mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $c) isa mention; $c isa organization, has is_dissolved true, has name $n; fetch { "title": $t, "company_name": $n };

question: Which investors have invested in companies located in 'San Francisco'?
cypher: MATCH (i:Organization)-[:INVESTED_IN]->(c:Company)-[:LOCATED_IN]->(city:City {name: 'San Francisco'}) RETURN DISTINCT i.name
typeql: match $city isa city, has city_name "San Francisco"; (located_org: $c, location_city: $city) isa location; (invested_org: $c, investor: $i) isa investment; $i has name $n; fetch { "name": $n };

question: Who are the first 3 CEOs of organizations that have a public status and a revenue above 1 billion?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_CEO]->(p:Person)
WHERE o.isPublic = true AND o.revenue > 1e9
RETURN p.name AS ceoName, o.name AS orgName
LIMIT 3
typeql: match $o isa organization, has is_public true, has revenue $r, has name $org_name; $r > 1000000000.0; (led_org: $o, ceo: $p) isa ceo_leadership; $p has name $ceo_name; limit 3; fetch { "ceoName": $ceo_name, "orgName": $org_name };

question: List the first 3 articles mentioning organizations with a CEO named 'Julie Spellman Sweet' and have a sentiment score below 0.5.
cypher:
MATCH (p:Person {name: 'Julie Spellman Sweet'})<-[:HAS_CEO]-(o:Organization)<-[:MENTIONS]-(a:Article)
WHERE a.sentiment < 0.5
RETURN a
LIMIT 3
typeql: match $p isa person, has name "Julie Spellman Sweet"; (led_org: $o, ceo: $p) isa ceo_leadership; (mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $o) isa mention; $a isa article, has sentiment $s, has title $t, has author $au, has date $d; $s < 0.5; limit 3; fetch { "title": $t, "author": $au, "sentiment": $s, "date": $d };

question: Which organizations based in 'Seattle' have more than 1000 employees and are public?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:IN_CITY]->(:City {name: 'Seattle'})
WHERE o.nbrEmployees > 1000 AND o.isPublic IS NOT NULL AND o.isPublic = true
RETURN o
typeql: match $c isa city, has city_name "Seattle"; (located_org: $o, location_city: $c) isa location; $o isa organization, has nbr_employees $e, has is_public true, has name $n, has summary $s; $e > 1000; fetch { "name": $n, "summary": $s, "nbr_employees": $e };

question: Find the first 3 organizations that have a CEO named 'Julie Spellman Sweet' and have a revenue above 1 billion.
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_CEO]->(p:Person {name: 'Julie Spellman Sweet'})
WHERE o.revenue > 1e9
RETURN o
LIMIT 3
typeql: match $p isa person, has name "Julie Spellman Sweet"; (led_org: $o, ceo: $p) isa ceo_leadership; $o isa organization, has revenue $r, has name $n, has summary $s; $r > 1000000000.0; limit 3; fetch { "name": $n, "summary": $s, "revenue": $r };

question: Identify the top 3 organizations that have a CEO and have been mentioned in the latest articles with a high sentiment score.
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_CEO]->(ceo:Person)
MATCH (article:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(o)
WHERE article.sentiment > 0.5
WITH o, max(article.date) AS latestDate
ORDER BY latestDate DESC
LIMIT 3
RETURN o.name AS organization, ceo.name AS ceo
typeql: match (led_org: $o, ceo: $ceo) isa ceo_leadership; $ceo has name $ceo_name; (mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $o) isa mention; $a has sentiment $s, has date $d; $s > 0.5; $o has name $org_name; sort $d desc; limit 3; fetch { "organization": $org_name, "ceo": $ceo_name };

question: Who are the first 3 board members of organizations that have a CEO and are based in 'United States of America'?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_CEO]->(:Person)
WHERE (o)-[:IN_CITY]->(:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(:Country {name: 'United States of America'})
WITH o
MATCH (o)-[:HAS_BOARD_MEMBER]->(boardMember:Person)
RETURN boardMember.name
LIMIT 3
typeql: match (led_org: $o, ceo: $ceo) isa ceo_leadership; (located_org: $o, location_city: $city) isa location; (located_city: $city, location_country: $country) isa country_location; $country has country_name "United States of America"; (governed_org: $o, board_member: $bm) isa board_membership; $bm has name $bm_name; limit 3; fetch { "boardMemberName": $bm_name };

question: List the first 3 organizations that have been mentioned in articles with a sentiment score above 0.7 and have a CEO named 'Julie Spellman Sweet'.
typeql: match (mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $o) isa mention; $a has sentiment $s; $s > 0.7; $p isa person, has name "Julie Spellman Sweet"; (led_org: $o, ceo: $p) isa ceo_leadership; $o has name $n; limit 3; fetch { "name": $n };

question: Which organizations based in 'United States of America' have a public status and more than 1000 employees?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:IN_CITY]->(:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(c:Country {name: 'United States of America'})
WHERE o.isPublic = true AND o.nbrEmployees > 1000
RETURN o
typeql: match (located_org: $o, location_city: $city) isa location; (located_city: $city, location_country: $country) isa country_location; $country has country_name "United States of America"; $o isa organization, has is_public true, has nbr_employees $e, has name $n, has summary $s; $e > 1000; fetch { "name": $n, "summary": $s, "nbr_employees": $e };

question: Find the first 3 organizations that have CEOs named 'Julie Spellman Sweet' and are based in 'Seattle'.
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_CEO]->(p:Person {name: 'Julie Spellman Sweet'})
WHERE (o)-[:IN_CITY]->(:City {name: 'Seattle'})
RETURN o
LIMIT 3
typeql: match $p isa person, has name "Julie Spellman Sweet"; (led_org: $o, ceo: $p) isa ceo_leadership; $c isa city, has city_name "Seattle"; (located_org: $o, location_city: $c) isa location; $o has name $n, has summary $s; limit 3; fetch { "name": $n, "summary": $s };

question: Identify the top 3 organizations that have been mentioned in articles authored by 'James Blackman'.
cypher:
MATCH (a:Article {author: 'James Blackman'})-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization)
RETURN o.name AS organization, count(*) AS mentions
ORDER BY mentions DESC
LIMIT 3
typeql: match $a isa article, has author "James Blackman"; (mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $o) isa mention; $o has name $org_name; reduce $mentions = count($o); sort $mentions desc; limit 3; fetch { "organization": $org_name, "mentions": $mentions };

question: Which companies have the same CEO as companies that are suppliers to 'Quantum Dynamics'?
cypher: MATCH (c1:Company)-[:CEO]->(ceo:Person)<-[:CEO]-(c2:Company)-[:SUPPLIES]->(c3:Company {name: 'Quantum Dynamics'}) RETURN DISTINCT c1.name AS company
typeql: match $c3 isa organization, has name "Quantum Dynamics"; (supplier_org: $c2, supplied_org: $c3) isa supply; (led_org: $c2, ceo: $ceo) isa ceo_leadership; (led_org: $c1, ceo: $ceo) isa ceo_leadership; $c1 has name $company; fetch { "company": $company };

question: Find the countries where companies with revenue over 500 billion are headquartered.
cypher: MATCH (c:Company)-[:LOCATED_IN]->(city:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(country:Country) WHERE c.revenue > 500000000000 RETURN DISTINCT country.name AS country
typeql: match $c isa organization, has revenue $r; $r > 500000000000; (located_org: $c, location_city: $city) isa location; (located_city: $city, location_country: $country) isa country_location; $country has country_name $cn; fetch { "country": $cn };

question: Which companies compete with subsidiaries of 'Global Holdings Corp'?
cypher: MATCH (parent:Company {name: 'Global Holdings Corp'})-[:SUBSIDIARY]->(sub:Company)-[:COMPETES_WITH]-(competitor:Company) RETURN DISTINCT competitor.name AS competitor
typeql: match $parent isa organization, has name "Global Holdings Corp"; (parent_org: $parent, subsidiary_org: $sub) isa subsidiary; (competitor: $sub, competitor: $competitor) isa competition; not { $sub is $competitor; }; $competitor has name $cn; fetch { "competitor": $cn };

question: Find articles that mention companies in the 'Healthcare' industry with positive sentiment.
cypher: MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(c:Company)-[:IN_CATEGORY]->(cat:IndustryCategory {name: 'Healthcare'}) WHERE a.sentiment = 'positive' RETURN a.title AS article, c.name AS company
typeql: match $cat isa industry_category, has industry_category_name "Healthcare"; (categorized_org: $c, category: $cat) isa categorization; (mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $c) isa mention; $a has sentiment $s, has title $t; $s > 0.5; $c has name $cn; fetch { "article": $t, "company": $cn };

question: Which public companies have board members who are also CEOs of other companies?
cypher: MATCH (c1:Company {is_public: true})-[:HAS_BOARD_MEMBER]->(p:Person)<-[:CEO]-(c2:Company) WHERE c1 <> c2 RETURN DISTINCT c1.name AS company, p.name AS board_member_ceo
typeql: match $c1 isa organization, has is_public true; (governed_org: $c1, board_member: $p) isa board_membership; (led_org: $c2, ceo: $p) isa ceo_leadership; not { $c1 is $c2; }; $c1 has name $company; $p has name $board_member_ceo; fetch { "company": $company, "board_member_ceo": $board_member_ceo };

question: Find companies that are both investors and suppliers in the same industry.
cypher: MATCH (c1:Company)-[:INVESTED_IN]->(c2:Company)-[:IN_CATEGORY]->(cat:IndustryCategory)<-[:IN_CATEGORY]-(c3:Company)<-[:SUPPLIES]-(c1) RETURN DISTINCT c1.name AS company, cat.name AS industry
typeql: match (invested_org: $c2, investor: $c1) isa investment; (categorized_org: $c2, category: $cat) isa categorization; (categorized_org: $c3, category: $cat) isa categorization; (supplier_org: $c1, supplied_org: $c3) isa supply; $c1 isa organization, has name $company; $cat has industry_category_name $industry; fetch { "company": $company, "industry": $industry };

question: Which dissolved companies had the highest revenue before dissolution?
cypher: MATCH (c:Company {is_dissolved: true}) RETURN c.name AS company, c.revenue AS revenue ORDER BY c.revenue DESC LIMIT 5
typeql: match $c isa organization, has is_dissolved true, has name $company, has revenue $revenue; sort $revenue desc; limit 5; fetch { "company": $company, "revenue": $revenue };

question: Find the parent companies of subsidiaries located in 'Tokyo'.
cypher: MATCH (parent:Company)-[:SUBSIDIARY]->(sub:Company)-[:LOCATED_IN]->(city:City {name: 'Tokyo'}) RETURN DISTINCT parent.name AS parent_company, sub.name AS subsidiary
typeql: match $city isa city, has city_name "Tokyo"; (located_org: $sub, location_city: $city) isa location; (parent_org: $parent, subsidiary_org: $sub) isa subsidiary; $parent has name $parent_company; $sub has name $subsidiary; fetch { "parent_company": $parent_company, "subsidiary": $subsidiary };

question: Which companies have been mentioned in articles by author 'Jane Smith'?
cypher: MATCH (a:Article {author: 'Jane Smith'})-[:MENTIONS]->(c:Company) RETURN DISTINCT c.name AS company
typeql: match $a isa article, has author "Jane Smith"; (mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $c) isa mention; $c has name $company; fetch { "company": $company };

question: Find companies that compete with more than 3 other companies.
cypher: MATCH (c:Company)-[:COMPETES_WITH]-(competitor:Company) WITH c, COUNT(DISTINCT competitor) AS num_competitors WHERE num_competitors > 3 RETURN c.name AS company, num_competitors ORDER BY num_competitors DESC
typeql: match $c isa organization, has name $company; (competitor: $c, competitor: $comp) isa competition; not { $c is $comp; }; reduce $num_competitors = count($comp); $num_competitors > 3; sort $num_competitors desc; fetch { "company": $company, "num_competitors": $num_competitors };

question: Find companies that are suppliers to other companies and have revenue greater than 500 million.
cypher: MATCH (c:Company)-[:SUPPLIES]->(other:Company) WHERE c.revenue > 500000000 RETURN DISTINCT c.name AS supplier_name, c.revenue AS revenue
typeql: match $c isa organization, has name $supplier_name, has revenue $revenue; (supplier_org: $c, supplied_org: $other) isa supply; $other isa organization; $revenue > 500000000; fetch { "supplier_name": $supplier_name, "revenue": $revenue };

question: List all articles mentioning companies in the technology industry.
cypher: MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(c:Company)-[:IN_CATEGORY]->(cat:IndustryCategory) WHERE cat.name = 'Technology' RETURN a.title AS article_title, c.name AS company_name
typeql: match $a isa article, has title $article_title; (mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $c) isa mention; $c isa organization, has name $company_name; (categorized_org: $c, category: $cat) isa categorization; $cat isa industry_category, has industry_category_name "Technology"; fetch { "article_title": $article_title, "company_name": $company_name };

question: Find all companies headquartered in cities located in Germany.
cypher: MATCH (c:Company)-[:LOCATED_IN]->(city:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(country:Country) WHERE country.name = 'Germany' RETURN c.name AS company_name, city.name AS city_name
typeql: match $c isa organization, has name $company_name; (located_org: $c, location_city: $city) isa location; $city isa city, has city_name $city_name; (located_city: $city, location_country: $country) isa country_location; $country isa country, has country_name "Germany"; fetch { "company_name": $company_name, "city_name": $city_name };

question: What are the names of CEOs who lead public companies?
cypher: MATCH (p:Person)-[:CEO_OF]->(c:Company) WHERE c.isPublic = true RETURN p.name AS ceo_name, c.name AS company_name

question: Find companies that have both a CEO and at least one board member.
cypher: MATCH (ceo:Person)-[:CEO_OF]->(c:Company)<-[:BOARD_MEMBER_OF]-(board:Person) RETURN DISTINCT c.name AS company_name, ceo.name AS ceo_name
typeql: match $ceo isa person, has name $ceo_name; (ceo: $ceo, led_org: $c) isa ceo_leadership; $c isa organization, has name $company_name; (governed_org: $c, board_member: $board) isa board_membership; $board isa person; fetch { "company_name": $company_name, "ceo_name": $ceo_name };

question: List all dissolved companies and their former CEOs.

question: Find articles with negative sentiment about companies in the finance industry.
cypher: MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(c:Company)-[:IN_CATEGORY]->(cat:IndustryCategory) WHERE cat.name = 'Finance' AND a.sentiment < 0 RETURN a.title AS article_title, a.sentiment AS sentiment, c.name AS company_name
typeql: match $a isa article, has title $article_title, has sentiment $sentiment; (mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $c) isa mention; $c isa organization, has name $company_name; (categorized_org: $c, category: $cat) isa categorization; $cat isa industry_category, has industry_category_name "Finance"; $sentiment < 0; fetch { "article_title": $article_title, "sentiment": $sentiment, "company_name": $company_name };

question: What companies are competitors with each other in the retail industry?
cypher: MATCH (c1:Company)-[:COMPETES_WITH]->(c2:Company), (c1)-[:IN_CATEGORY]->(cat:IndustryCategory) WHERE cat.name = 'Retail' RETURN c1.name AS company1, c2.name AS company2
typeql: match $c1 isa organization, has name $company1; $c2 isa organization, has name $company2; (competitor: $c1, competitor: $c2) isa competition; (categorized_org: $c1, category: $cat) isa categorization; $cat isa industry_category, has industry_category_name "Retail"; fetch { "company1": $company1, "company2": $company2 };

question: Find all subsidiaries of companies that have more than 10000 employees.
cypher: MATCH (parent:Company)-[:SUBSIDIARY]->(sub:Company) WHERE parent.nbrEmployees > 10000 RETURN parent.name AS parent_company, sub.name AS subsidiary, parent.nbrEmployees AS parent_employees
typeql: match $parent isa organization, has name $parent_company, has nbr_employees $parent_employees; (parent_org: $parent, subsidiary_org: $sub) isa subsidiary; $sub isa organization, has name $subsidiary; $parent_employees > 10000; fetch { "parent_company": $parent_company, "subsidiary": $subsidiary, "parent_employees": $parent_employees };

question: List all persons who are both a CEO and a board member of different companies.
cypher: MATCH (p:Person)-[:CEO_OF]->(c1:Company), (p)-[:BOARD_MEMBER_OF]->(c2:Company) WHERE c1 <> c2 RETURN p.name AS person_name, c1.name AS ceo_of, c2.name AS board_member_of
typeql: match $p isa person, has name $person_name; (ceo: $p, led_org: $c1) isa ceo_leadership; $c1 isa organization, has name $ceo_of; (governed_org: $c2, board_member: $p) isa board_membership; $c2 isa organization, has name $board_member_of; not { $c1 is $c2; }; fetch { "person_name": $person_name, "ceo_of": $ceo_of, "board_member_of": $board_member_of };

question: Which organizations are competitors to 'SAP'?

question: List the first 3 organizations that were mentioned in articles published in 2022.
cypher:
MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization)
WHERE a.date >= date("2022-01-01") AND a.date < date("2023-01-01")
RETURN o.name
LIMIT 3
typeql: match $a isa article, has date $d; $o isa organization, has name $n; (mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $o) isa mention; $d >= 2022-01-01T00:00:00; $d < 2023-01-01T00:00:00; limit 3; fetch { "name": $n };

question: What is the sentiment of the article that has the highest sentiment score mentioning 'Accenture'?

RETURN a.title AS article, a.sentiment AS sentiment
ORDER BY a.sentiment DESC
LIMIT 1
typeql: match $a isa article, has title $t, has sentiment $s; $o isa organization, has name "Accenture"; (mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $o) isa mention; sort $s desc; limit 1; fetch { "article": $t, "sentiment": $s };

question: Which organizations have a motto containing the word 'technology'?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)
WHERE o.motto CONTAINS 'technology'
RETURN o.name AS organization, o.motto AS motto
typeql: match $o isa organization, has name $n, has motto $m; $m like "%technology%"; fetch { "organization": $n, "motto": $m };

question: List the organizations that have more than one subsidiary.
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)
WHERE exists {
  (o)-[:HAS_SUBSIDIARY]->(:Organization)
  AND
  size((o)-[:HAS_SUBSIDIARY]->(:Organization)) > 1
}
RETURN o.name AS organization, count((o)-[:HAS_SUBSIDIARY]->()) AS subsidiaryCount
typeql: match $o isa organization, has name $n; (parent_org: $o, subsidiary_org: $s1) isa subsidiary; (parent_org: $o, subsidiary_org: $s2) isa subsidiary; not { $s1 is $s2; }; reduce $count = count($s1) groupby $n;

question: Which countries host organizations that have a revenue over 50 million?

WHERE o.revenue > 5e7

typeql: match $o isa organization, has revenue $r; $r > 50000000.0; (located_org: $o, location_city: $city) isa location; (located_city: $city, location_country: $c) isa country_location; $c has country_name $cn; fetch { "country": $cn };

question: What are the industry categories of organizations located in 'Seattle'?

RETURN DISTINCT c.name

question: Who wrote the article with the highest sentiment score mentioning 'SAP'?

ORDER BY a.sentiment DESC
LIMIT 1
RETURN a.author AS author
typeql: match $a isa article, has sentiment $s, has author $auth; $o isa organization, has name "SAP"; (mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $o) isa mention; sort $s desc; limit 1; fetch { "author": $auth };

question: What are the first 3 articles about organizations with a public status?

RETURN a.title AS article, o.name AS organization
ORDER BY a.date DESC
LIMIT 3
typeql: match $a isa article, has title $t, has date $d; $o isa organization, has is_public true, has name $org_name; (mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $o) isa mention; sort $d desc; limit 3; fetch { "article": $t, "organization": $org_name };

question: What organizations are headquartered in cities that are in the 'United States of America'?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:IN_CITY]->(c:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(country:Country {name: 'United States of America'})
RETURN o.name AS organization, c.name AS city
typeql: match $o isa organization, has name $org_name; (located_org: $o, location_city: $c) isa location; $c has city_name $cn; (located_city: $c, location_country: $country) isa country_location; $country has country_name "United States of America"; fetch { "organization": $org_name, "city": $cn };

question: Which city has the most organizations with public status?

MATCH (c:City)<-[:IN_CITY]-(o:Organization)

WITH c, count(o) AS publicOrgCount

ORDER BY publicOrgCount DESC
LIMIT 1
typeql: match $c isa city, has city_name $cn; $o isa organization, has is_public true; (located_org: $o, location_city: $c) isa location; reduce $count = count($o), group $cn; sort $count desc; limit 1; fetch { "city": $cn, "publicOrgCount": $count };

question: Who are the children of 'Julie Spellman Sweet'?

question: What are the first 3 organizations mentioned in articles from 'MrWeb'?

question: What is the summary description of the organization with the lowest number of employees?

ORDER BY o.nbrEmployees
LIMIT 1
