question: List the top 5 countries by the number of organizations headquartered there.
cypher:
MATCH (c:Country)<-[:IN_COUNTRY]-(city:City)<-[:IN_CITY]-(o:Organization)
WITH c, count(o) AS numOrgs
ORDER BY numOrgs DESC
LIMIT 5
RETURN c.name AS country, numOrgs
typeql: match $c isa country, has country_name $cn; $city isa city; (located_city: $city, location_country: $c) isa country_location; $o isa organization; (located_org: $o, location_city: $city) isa location; reduce $count = count($o), group $cn; sort $count desc; limit 5; fetch { "country": $cn, "numOrgs": $count };

question: Which cities have more than two industries represented by organizations within them?
cypher:
MATCH (c:City)<-[:IN_CITY]-(o:Organization)-[:HAS_CATEGORY]->(i:IndustryCategory)
WITH c, count(DISTINCT i) AS industryCount
WHERE industryCount > 2
RETURN c.name AS city, industryCount
typeql: match $c isa city, has city_name $cn; $o isa organization; (located_org: $o, location_city: $c) isa location; $i isa industry_category; (categorized_org: $o, category: $i) isa categorization; reduce $count = count($i), group $cn; $count > 2; fetch { "city": $cn, "industryCount": $count };

question: What are the top 3 industries by the number of organizations in each?
cypher:
MATCH (ic:IndustryCategory)<-[:HAS_CATEGORY]-(o:Organization)
RETURN ic.name AS industry, count(o) AS numOrganizations
ORDER BY numOrganizations DESC
LIMIT 3
typeql: match $ic isa industry_category, has industry_category_name $icn; $o isa organization; (categorized_org: $o, category: $ic) isa categorization; reduce $count = count($o), group $icn; sort $count desc; limit 3; fetch { "industry": $icn, "numOrganizations": $count };

question: Which companies are suppliers to organizations that have been mentioned in articles with negative sentiment?
cypher: MATCH (s:Organization)-[:SUPPLIES]->(o:Organization)<-[:MENTIONS]-(a:Article) WHERE a.sentiment < 0 RETURN DISTINCT s.name AS supplier_name
typeql: match $s isa organization, has name $supplier_name; $o isa organization; $a isa article, has sentiment $sent; $sent < 0; (supplier_org: $s, supplied_org: $o) isa supply; (mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $o) isa mention; fetch { "supplier_name": $supplier_name };

question: Which public companies have invested in dissolved organizations?
cypher: MATCH (investor:Organization)-[:HAS_INVESTED_IN]->(target:Organization) WHERE investor.isPublic = true AND target.isDissolved = true RETURN investor.name AS investor_name, target.name AS dissolved_company
typeql: match $investor isa organization, has is_public true, has name $investor_name; $target isa organization, has is_dissolved true, has name $dissolved_name; (invested_org: $target, investor: $investor) isa investment; fetch { "investor_name": $investor_name, "dissolved_company": $dissolved_name };

question: List all board members who serve on organizations in the Technology industry category.
cypher: MATCH (p:Person)-[:BOARD_MEMBER_OF]->(o:Organization)-[:IN_CATEGORY]->(c:IndustryCategory) WHERE c.name = 'Technology' RETURN DISTINCT p.name AS board_member
typeql: match $p isa person, has name $board_member; $o isa organization; $c isa industry_category, has industry_category_name "Technology"; (board_member: $p, governed_org: $o) isa board_membership; (categorized_org: $o, category: $c) isa categorization; fetch { "board_member": $board_member };

question: Find organizations that are both competitors and have a supplier-customer relationship.
cypher: MATCH (o1:Organization)-[:COMPETES_WITH]->(o2:Organization) MATCH (o1)-[:SUPPLIES]->(o2) RETURN o1.name AS org1, o2.name AS org2
typeql: match $o1 isa organization, has name $org1_name; $o2 isa organization, has name $org2_name; (competitor: $o1, competitor: $o2) isa competition; (supplier_org: $o1, supplied_org: $o2) isa supply; fetch { "org1": $org1_name, "org2": $org2_name };

question: Find all articles that mention organizations with revenue greater than 1 billion.
cypher: MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization) WHERE o.revenue > 1000000000 RETURN a.title AS article_title, o.name AS organization, o.revenue AS revenue
typeql: match $a isa article, has title $article_title; $o isa organization, has name $org_name, has revenue $rev; $rev > 1000000000; (mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $o) isa mention; fetch { "article_title": $article_title, "organization": $org_name, "revenue": $rev };

question: List parent-child relationships between people where the parent is a CEO.
cypher: MATCH (parent:Person)-[:PARENT_OF]->(child:Person), (parent)-[:CEO_OF]->(o:Organization) RETURN parent.name AS ceo_parent, child.name AS child_name, o.name AS organization
typeql: match $parent isa person, has name $parent_name; $child isa person, has name $child_name; $o isa organization, has name $org_name; (parent: $parent, child: $child) isa parent_child; (ceo: $parent, led_org: $o) isa ceo_leadership; fetch { "ceo_parent": $parent_name, "child_name": $child_name, "organization": $org_name };

question: Which organizations in the Finance category have received investments from Technology companies?
cypher: MATCH (tech:Organization)-[:IN_CATEGORY]->(tc:IndustryCategory), (tech)-[:HAS_INVESTED_IN]->(fin:Organization)-[:IN_CATEGORY]->(fc:IndustryCategory) WHERE tc.name = 'Technology' AND fc.name = 'Finance' RETURN fin.name AS finance_org, tech.name AS tech_investor
typeql: match $tech isa organization, has name $tech_name; $fin isa organization, has name $fin_name; $tc isa industry_category, has industry_category_name "Technology"; $fc isa industry_category, has industry_category_name "Finance"; (categorized_org: $tech, category: $tc) isa categorization; (categorized_org: $fin, category: $fc) isa categorization; (invested_org: $fin, investor: $tech) isa investment; fetch { "finance_org": $fin_name, "tech_investor": $tech_name };

question: Find all organizations that have no CEO assigned.
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization) WHERE NOT EXISTS { MATCH (p:Person)-[:CEO_OF]->(o) } RETURN o.name AS organization_without_ceo
typeql: match $o isa organization, has name $org_name; not { (ceo: $p, led_org: $o) isa ceo_leadership; }; fetch { "organization_without_ceo": $org_name };

question: Which organizations have been mentioned in articles with a negative sentiment?
cypher: MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization) WHERE a.sentiment = 'negative' RETURN DISTINCT o.name AS organization
typeql: match $a isa article, has sentiment $s; $s < 0.5; (mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $o) isa mention; $o isa organization, has name $n; fetch { "organization": $n };

question: List all public companies that are subsidiaries of other companies.
cypher: MATCH (parent:Organization)-[:HAS_SUBSIDIARY]->(sub:Organization) WHERE sub.isPublic = true RETURN sub.name AS subsidiary, parent.name AS parent_company
typeql: match $parent isa organization, has name $pn; $sub isa organization, has name $sn, has is_public true; (parent_org: $parent, subsidiary_org: $sub) isa subsidiary; fetch { "subsidiary": $sn, "parent_company": $pn };

question: Which organizations have invested in companies located in Japan?
cypher: MATCH (investor:Organization)-[:INVESTED_IN]->(target:Organization)-[:LOCATED_IN]->(c:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(country:Country) WHERE country.name = 'Japan' RETURN DISTINCT investor.name AS investor, target.name AS target_company
typeql: match $investor isa organization, has name $in; $target isa organization, has name $tn; (investor: $investor, invested_org: $target) isa investment; (located_org: $target, location_city: $c) isa location; $c isa city; (located_city: $c, location_country: $country) isa country_location; $country isa country, has country_name "Japan"; fetch { "investor": $in, "target_company": $tn };

question: Find all CEOs who lead organizations with more than 10000 employees.
cypher: MATCH (p:Person)-[:CEO_OF]->(o:Organization) WHERE o.nbrEmployees > 10000 RETURN p.name AS ceo, o.name AS organization, o.nbrEmployees AS employees
typeql: match $p isa person, has name $pn; $o isa organization, has name $on, has nbr_employees $e; $e > 10000; (ceo: $p, led_org: $o) isa ceo_leadership; fetch { "ceo": $pn, "organization": $on, "employees": $e };

question: Which board members serve on multiple organization boards?
cypher: MATCH (p:Person)-[:BOARD_MEMBER_OF]->(o:Organization) WITH p, COUNT(o) AS board_count WHERE board_count > 1 RETURN p.name AS board_member, board_count ORDER BY board_count DESC
typeql: match $p isa person, has name $n; (board_member: $p, governed_org: $o) isa board_membership; reduce $board_count = count($o), group($p, $n); $board_count > 1; sort $board_count desc; fetch { "board_member": $n, "board_count": $board_count };

question: List organizations in the Technology category that compete with each other.
cypher: MATCH (o1:Organization)-[:IN_CATEGORY]->(c:IndustryCategory {name: 'Technology'}), (o2:Organization)-[:IN_CATEGORY]->(c), (o1)-[:COMPETITOR_OF]->(o2) RETURN o1.name AS company1, o2.name AS company2
typeql: match $c isa industry_category, has industry_category_name "Technology"; $o1 isa organization, has name $n1; $o2 isa organization, has name $n2; (categorized_org: $o1, category: $c) isa categorization; (categorized_org: $o2, category: $c) isa categorization; (competitor: $o1, competitor: $o2) isa competition; fetch { "company1": $n1, "company2": $n2 };

question: Find suppliers of dissolved organizations.
cypher: MATCH (supplier:Organization)-[:SUPPLIES]->(dissolved:Organization) WHERE dissolved.isDissolved = true RETURN supplier.name AS supplier, dissolved.name AS dissolved_company
typeql: match $supplier isa organization, has name $sn; $dissolved isa organization, has name $dn, has is_dissolved true; (supplier_org: $supplier, supplied_org: $dissolved) isa supply; fetch { "supplier": $sn, "dissolved_company": $dn };

question: Which cities host organizations with revenue over 1 billion?
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)-[:LOCATED_IN]->(c:City) WHERE o.revenue > 1000000000 RETURN DISTINCT c.name AS city, COUNT(o) AS high_revenue_orgs ORDER BY high_revenue_orgs DESC
typeql: match $o isa organization, has revenue $r; $r > 1000000000.0; (located_org: $o, location_city: $c) isa location; $c isa city, has city_name $cn; reduce $high_revenue_orgs = count($o), group($c, $cn); sort $high_revenue_orgs desc; fetch { "city": $cn, "high_revenue_orgs": $high_revenue_orgs };

question: Find parent companies and all their subsidiaries' CEOs.
cypher: MATCH (parent:Organization)-[:HAS_SUBSIDIARY]->(sub:Organization)<-[:CEO_OF]-(ceo:Person) RETURN parent.name AS parent_company, sub.name AS subsidiary, ceo.name AS ceo
typeql: match $parent isa organization, has name $pn; $sub isa organization, has name $sn; $ceo isa person, has name $cn; (parent_org: $parent, subsidiary_org: $sub) isa subsidiary; (ceo: $ceo, led_org: $sub) isa ceo_leadership; fetch { "parent_company": $pn, "subsidiary": $sn, "ceo": $cn };

question: List articles mentioning organizations that have received investments.
cypher: MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization)<-[:INVESTED_IN]-(investor:Organization) RETURN DISTINCT a.title AS article, o.name AS mentioned_org, investor.name AS investor
typeql: match $a isa article, has title $t; $o isa organization, has name $on; $investor isa organization, has name $in; (mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $o) isa mention; (investor: $investor, invested_org: $o) isa investment; fetch { "article": $t, "mentioned_org": $on, "investor": $in };

question: What are the names of 3 industry categories that the most organizations belong to?
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)-[:IN_CATEGORY]->(c:IndustryCategory) RETURN c.name AS category, COUNT(o) AS organizationCount ORDER BY organizationCount DESC LIMIT 3

question: List the names of 3 organizations that are suppliers to technology companies
cypher: MATCH (o1:Organization)-[:SUPPLIES]->(o2:Organization)-[:IN_CATEGORY]->(c:IndustryCategory {name: 'technology'}) RETURN o1.name AS supplierName LIMIT 3

question: Which 3 cities are mentioned most frequently in articles?
cypher: MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization)-[:LOCATED_IN]->(city:City) RETURN city.name AS cityName, COUNT(a) AS mentionCount ORDER BY mentionCount DESC LIMIT 3

question: Who are the board members of the first 3 organizations with public ownership?
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization {isPublic: true})<-[:MEMBER_OF]-(p:Person) RETURN o.name AS organization, p.name AS boardMember LIMIT 3

question: What are the names of the first 3 organizations that have subsidiaries?
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_SUBSIDIARY]->(s:Organization) RETURN DISTINCT o.name AS parentOrganization LIMIT 3

question: Which 3 countries have the most cities with organizations based in them?
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)-[:LOCATED_IN]->(city:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(country:Country) RETURN country.name AS countryName, COUNT(DISTINCT city) AS cityCount ORDER BY cityCount DESC LIMIT 3

question: Name 3 organizations that are competitors in the software industry
cypher: MATCH (o1:Organization)-[:COMPETES_WITH]->(o2:Organization), (o1)-[:IN_CATEGORY]->(c:IndustryCategory {name: 'software'}) RETURN o1.name AS competitor1, o2.name AS competitor2 LIMIT 3

question: What are the names of the first 3 organizations that are investors in companies in the healthcare industry?
cypher: MATCH (investor:Organization)-[:HAS_INVESTED_IN]->(o:Organization)-[:IN_CATEGORY]->(c:IndustryCategory {name: 'healthcare'}) RETURN investor.name AS investorName LIMIT 3

question: Which 3 people have the most children listed in the database?
cypher: MATCH (p:Person)-[:PARENT_OF]->(child:Person) RETURN p.name AS parentName, COUNT(child) AS childrenCount ORDER BY childrenCount DESC LIMIT 3

question: Name the first 3 organizations that have at least one board member and one investor
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)<-[:MEMBER_OF]-(p:Person), (investor:Organization)-[:HAS_INVESTED_IN]->(o) RETURN DISTINCT o.name AS organizationName LIMIT 3

question: List the top 5 cities where the headquarters of public organizations are located
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization {isPublic: true})-[:LOCATED_IN]->(city:City) RETURN city.name AS cityName, COUNT(o) AS organizationCount ORDER BY organizationCount DESC LIMIT 5

question: Who are the first 3 CEOs of organizations in the manufacturing industry?
cypher: MATCH (p:Person)-[:CEO_OF]->(o:Organization)-[:IN_CATEGORY]->(c:IndustryCategory {name: 'manufacturing'}) RETURN p.name AS ceoName, o.name AS organizationName LIMIT 3

question: Name 3 organizations that have been mentioned in articles with a positive sentiment
cypher: MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization) WHERE a.sentiment = 'positive' RETURN o.name AS organizationName LIMIT 3

question: Which 3 industry categories have the most organizations with a revenue greater than 10 billion?
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)-[:IN_CATEGORY]->(c:IndustryCategory) WHERE o.revenue > 10000000000 RETURN c.name AS category, COUNT(o) AS organizationCount ORDER BY organizationCount DESC LIMIT 3

question: What are the names of the organizations where the CEOs have a summary mentioning 'innovation'?
cypher: MATCH (p:Person)-[:CEO_OF]->(o:Organization) WHERE p.summary CONTAINS 'innovation' RETURN o.name AS organizationName

question: Which 3 organizations have the highest number of investors?
cypher: MATCH (investor:Organization)-[:HAS_INVESTED_IN]->(o:Organization) RETURN o.name AS organizationName, COUNT(investor) AS investorCount ORDER BY investorCount DESC LIMIT 3

question: Name the first 3 organizations that have been mentioned in at least 5 articles
cypher: MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization) WITH o, COUNT(a) AS mentionCount WHERE mentionCount >= 5 RETURN o.name AS organizationName LIMIT 3

question: What are the names of 3 organizations that have been dissolved?
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization) WHERE o.status = 'dissolved' RETURN o.name AS organizationName LIMIT 3

question: Which 3 countries are mentioned the most in articles regarding organizations in the finance industry?
cypher: MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization)-[:IN_CATEGORY]->(c:IndustryCategory {name: 'finance'}), (o)-[:LOCATED_IN]->(city:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(country:Country) RETURN country.name AS countryName, COUNT(a) AS mentionCount ORDER BY mentionCount DESC LIMIT 3

question: What are the names of organizations that have both a subsidiary and an investor?
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_SUBSIDIARY]->(s:Organization), (investor:Organization)-[:HAS_INVESTED_IN]->(o) RETURN DISTINCT o.name AS organizationName

question: List the top 5 organizations that have a subsidiary in a different country
cypher: MATCH (o1:Organization)-[:LOCATED_IN]->(city1:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(country1:Country), (o1)-[:HAS_SUBSIDIARY]->(o2:Organization)-[:LOCATED_IN]->(city2:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(country2:Country) WHERE country1 <> country2 RETURN o1.name AS organization, country1.name AS homeCountry, o2.name AS subsidiary, country2.name AS subsidiaryCountry LIMIT 5

question: Who are the first 3 children of people who are CEOs of public companies?
cypher: MATCH (ceo:Person)-[:CEO_OF]->(o:Organization {isPublic: true}), (ceo)-[:PARENT_OF]->(child:Person) RETURN ceo.name AS ceoName, child.name AS childName LIMIT 3

question: Name the top 3 organizations by number of articles mentioning them that are based in the US
cypher: MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization)-[:LOCATED_IN]->(city:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(country:Country {name: 'United States'}) RETURN o.name AS organizationName, COUNT(a) AS mentionCount ORDER BY mentionCount DESC LIMIT 3

question: List the first 3 organizations that have a CEO and a board member who are related
cypher: MATCH (ceo:Person)-[:CEO_OF]->(o:Organization)<-[:MEMBER_OF]-(member:Person), (ceo)-[:PARENT_OF|CHILD_OF*1..2]-(member) RETURN DISTINCT o.name AS organizationName LIMIT 3

question: Which 3 cities are the most frequently mentioned settings for articles about finance companies?
cypher: MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization)-[:IN_CATEGORY]->(c:IndustryCategory {name: 'finance'}), (o)-[:LOCATED_IN]->(city:City) RETURN city.name AS cityName, COUNT(a) AS articleCount ORDER BY articleCount DESC LIMIT 3

question: What are the names of the first 3 industry categories that have at least 5 organizations?
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)-[:IN_CATEGORY]->(c:IndustryCategory) WITH c, COUNT(o) AS orgCount WHERE orgCount >= 5 RETURN c.name AS categoryName LIMIT 3

question: Which 3 countries have organizations that are major players in the energy sector?
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)-[:IN_CATEGORY]->(c:IndustryCategory {name: 'energy'}), (o)-[:LOCATED_IN]->(city:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(country:Country) RETURN DISTINCT country.name AS countryName LIMIT 3

question: Which 3 people are mentioned as investors in multiple organizations?
cypher: MATCH (p:Person)-[:HAS_INVESTED_IN]->(o:Organization) WITH p, COUNT(o) AS investmentCount WHERE investmentCount > 1 RETURN p.name AS investorName, investmentCount ORDER BY investmentCount DESC LIMIT 3

question: List the names of the first 3 organizations that have a subsidiary with revenue greater than 1 billion
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_SUBSIDIARY]->(s:Organization) WHERE s.revenue > 1000000000 RETURN o.name AS parentOrganization, s.name AS subsidiaryName, s.revenue AS subsidiaryRevenue LIMIT 3

question: Name the first 3 organizations that have been dissolved and were in the retail industry
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)-[:IN_CATEGORY]->(c:IndustryCategory {name: 'retail'}) WHERE o.status = 'dissolved' RETURN o.name AS organizationName LIMIT 3

question: What are the names of 3 organizations that have a CEO who is also a board member of another organization?
cypher: MATCH (ceo:Person)-[:CEO_OF]->(o1:Organization), (ceo)-[:MEMBER_OF]->(o2:Organization) WHERE o1 <> o2 RETURN o1.name AS ceoOrganization, ceo.name AS ceoName, o2.name AS boardMemberOrganization LIMIT 3

question: Which 3 organizations have the most articles mentioning them?
cypher: MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization) RETURN o.name AS organizationName, COUNT(a) AS articleCount ORDER BY articleCount DESC LIMIT 3

question: Who are the first 3 people who have both parent and child relationships in the database?
cypher: MATCH (p:Person)-[:PARENT_OF]->(child:Person), (parent:Person)-[:PARENT_OF]->(p) RETURN p.name AS personName, parent.name AS parentName, child.name AS childName LIMIT 3

question: Name the first 3 cities that have organizations with revenue greater than 5 billion
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)-[:LOCATED_IN]->(city:City) WHERE o.revenue > 5000000000 RETURN DISTINCT city.name AS cityName LIMIT 3

question: What are the names of organizations that have a CEO who has children?
cypher: MATCH (ceo:Person)-[:CEO_OF]->(o:Organization), (ceo)-[:PARENT_OF]->(child:Person) RETURN DISTINCT o.name AS organizationName

question: Which 3 organizations have the most board members?
cypher: MATCH (p:Person)-[:MEMBER_OF]->(o:Organization) RETURN o.name AS organizationName, COUNT(p) AS boardMemberCount ORDER BY boardMemberCount DESC LIMIT 3

question: List the first 3 articles that mention new energy technology organizations
cypher: MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization)-[:IN_CATEGORY]->(c:IndustryCategory) WHERE c.name CONTAINS 'energy' RETURN a.title AS articleTitle, o.name AS organizationName LIMIT 3

question: Name the top 3 organizations in terms of number of times they are mentioned in article chunks
cypher: MATCH (c:Chunk)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization) RETURN o.name AS organizationName, COUNT(c) AS mentionCount ORDER BY mentionCount DESC LIMIT 3

question: Which 3 organizations have CEOs who have written articles about their industry?
cypher: MATCH (ceo:Person)-[:CEO_OF]->(o:Organization)-[:IN_CATEGORY]->(c:IndustryCategory), (ceo)-[:WROTE]->(a:Article) WHERE a.content CONTAINS c.name RETURN o.name AS organizationName, ceo.name AS ceoName, a.title AS articleTitle LIMIT 3

question: List the first 3 organizations that are both suppliers and competitors
cypher: MATCH (o1:Organization)-[:SUPPLIES]->(o2:Organization), (o1)-[:COMPETES_WITH]->(o2) RETURN o1.name AS organization1, o2.name AS organization2 LIMIT 3

question: Which 3 organizations have the most subsidiaries in the technology sector?
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_SUBSIDIARY]->(s:Organization)-[:IN_CATEGORY]->(c:IndustryCategory) WHERE c.name CONTAINS 'technology' OR c.name CONTAINS 'software' RETURN o.name AS parentOrganization, COUNT(s) AS subsidiaryCount ORDER BY subsidiaryCount DESC LIMIT 3

question: Name the first 3 public organizations that have competitors
cypher: MATCH (o1:Organization {isPublic: true})-[:COMPETES_WITH]->(o2:Organization) RETURN o1.name AS organization, o2.name AS competitor LIMIT 3

question: List the top 5 investors by number of investments
cypher: MATCH (investor)-[:HAS_INVESTED_IN]->(o:Organization) RETURN investor.name AS investorName, COUNT(o) AS investmentCount ORDER BY investmentCount DESC LIMIT 5

question: Which 3 cities have the most technology companies?
cypher: MATCH (o:Organization)-[:LOCATED_IN]->(city:City), (o)-[:IN_CATEGORY]->(c:IndustryCategory) WHERE c.name CONTAINS 'technology' OR c.name CONTAINS 'software' RETURN city.name AS cityName, COUNT(o) AS companyCount ORDER BY companyCount DESC LIMIT 3

question: Name the first 3 organizations that have a CEO, board members, and investors
cypher: MATCH (ceo:Person)-[:CEO_OF]->(o:Organization)<-[:MEMBER_OF]-(member:Person), (investor)-[:HAS_INVESTED_IN]->(o) RETURN DISTINCT o.name AS organizationName LIMIT 3

question: List the names of the first 3 organizations that have invested in startups in the past year.
Which 3 cities have the most organizations in the food industry?
cypher:
MATCH (c:City)<-[:IN_CITY]-(o:Organization)-[:HAS_CATEGORY]->(ic:IndustryCategory)
WHERE ic.name CONTAINS 'Food'
WITH c, count(o) as orgCount
ORDER BY orgCount DESC
LIMIT 3
RETURN c.name as city, orgCount

question: List the names of organizations that have a CEO and an investor who are siblings.
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_CEO]->(ceo:Person),
      (o)-[:HAS_INVESTOR]->(investor:Person),
      (ceo)-[:HAS_PARENT]->(parent:Person)<-[:HAS_PARENT]-(investor)
WHERE ceo <> investor
RETURN o.name AS organization

question: Name the first 3 organizations that are headquartered in capital cities and are in the telecommunications industry.
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:IN_CITY]->(c:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(country:Country)
WHERE c.name = country.name
  AND (o)-[:HAS_CATEGORY]->(:IndustryCategory {name: 'Telecommunications'})
RETURN o.name
LIMIT 3

question: List the top 3 articles that focus on the impact of technology on education.
cypher:
MATCH (a:Article)-[:HAS_CHUNK]->(c:Chunk)
WHERE c.text CONTAINS 'technology' AND c.text CONTAINS 'education'
WITH a, count(c) AS relevance
ORDER BY relevance DESC
LIMIT 3
RETURN a.title AS article, a.summary AS summary

question: Name the first 3 organizations that have both a CEO and a board member from the same family.
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_CEO]->(ceo:Person),
      (o)-[:HAS_BOARD_MEMBER]->(board_member:Person),
      (ceo)-[:HAS_PARENT|HAS_CHILD*]-(board_member)
RETURN o.name AS organization, ceo.name AS ceo, board_member.name AS board_member
LIMIT 3

question: Which 3 organizations have been involved in the most legal disputes according to articles?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)<-[:MENTIONS]-(a:Article)
WHERE a.title CONTAINS 'legal' OR a.title CONTAINS 'lawsuit' OR a.title CONTAINS 'dispute'
WITH o, count(a) AS numMentions
ORDER BY numMentions DESC
LIMIT 3
RETURN o.name AS organization, numMentions

question: List the names of the first 3 organizations that have more than 10,000 employees.
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)
WHERE o.nbrEmployees > 10000
RETURN o.name
LIMIT 3

question: Name the top 3 countries by number of organizations that have been mentioned in articles related to healthcare.
cypher:
MATCH (c:Country)<-[:IN_COUNTRY]-(city:City)<-[:IN_CITY]-(o:Organization)<-[:MENTIONS]-(a:Article)
WHERE (o)-[:HAS_CATEGORY]->(:IndustryCategory {name: 'Healthcare'})
RETURN c.name AS country, count(o) AS orgCount
ORDER BY orgCount DESC
LIMIT 3

question: Which 3 organizations have the most articles mentioning them with a sentiment score below 0.3?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)<-[:MENTIONS]-(a:Article)
WHERE a.sentiment < 0.3
WITH o, count(a) AS negArticleCount
ORDER BY negArticleCount DESC
LIMIT 3
RETURN o.name AS organization, negArticleCount

question: List the names of 3 organizations that have a motto related to sustainability.
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)
WHERE o.motto CONTAINS 'sustainability' OR o.motto CONTAINS 'sustainable'
RETURN o.name
LIMIT 3

question: Name the first 3 organizations that have been involved in mergers in the past 5 years.
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)
WHERE EXISTS {
  (o)-[:HAS_SUBSIDIARY|HAS_INVESTOR|HAS_SUPPLIER]->(:Organization)
  WHERE o.name IS NOT NULL
}
WITH o
ORDER BY o.name
LIMIT 3
RETURN o.name AS organization

question: Which 3 cities are most frequently cited in articles about urban development?
cypher:
MATCH (a:Article)-[:HAS_CHUNK]->(c:Chunk), (a)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization)-[:IN_CITY]->(city:City)
WHERE c.text CONTAINS 'urban development'
RETURN city.name, count(*) as frequency
ORDER BY frequency DESC
LIMIT 3

question: List the names of 3 organizations that have at least one female board member.
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_BOARD_MEMBER]->(p:Person)
WHERE p.name =~ ".*a" OR p.name =~ ".*e"
WITH o, count(p) AS num_female_board_members
WHERE num_female_board_members > 0
RETURN o.name
LIMIT 3

question: Name the top 3 organizations in terms of revenue that are headquartered in countries with developing economies.
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:IN_CITY]->(:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(c:Country)
WHERE c.name IN ['China', 'India', 'Brazil', 'Russia', 'Mexico', 'Indonesia', 'Turkey']
  AND o.revenue IS NOT NULL
RETURN o.name AS organization, o.revenue AS revenue
ORDER BY o.revenue DESC
LIMIT 3

question: Which 3 organizations have been featured in the most articles about market expansions?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)<-[:MENTIONS]-(a:Article)
WHERE a.title CONTAINS 'market expansion'
WITH o, count(a) as articleCount
ORDER BY articleCount DESC
LIMIT 3
RETURN o.name as organization, articleCount

question: List the first 3 articles that mention organizations with a significant number of layoffs in the past year.
cypher:
MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization)
WHERE o.nbrEmployees IS NOT NULL
  AND exists {
    (o)-[:HAS_SUBSIDIARY*]->(sub:Organization)
    WHERE sub.nbrEmployees < o.nbrEmployees * 0.9
  }
RETURN a.title, a.summary, a.date
ORDER BY a.date DESC
LIMIT 3

question: Which 3 organizations have the most subsidiaries in different industries?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_SUBSIDIARY]->(sub:Organization)
WHERE sub.id <> o.id
WITH o, count(DISTINCT sub.id) AS numSubs, collect(DISTINCT sub.id) AS subIds
WITH o, numSubs, size(apoc.coll.toSet([(sub)-[:HAS_CATEGORY]->(c) | c.name])) AS numIndustries, subIds
ORDER BY numIndustries DESC
LIMIT 3
RETURN o.name AS organization, numSubs, numIndustries, subIds

question: Name the first 3 organizations that are involved in more than one industry category and have subsidiaries in at least two different countries.
cypher:

WHERE categoryCount > 1

WHERE size(countries) >= 2

LIMIT 3

question: Which organizations have a CEO who is also an investor in other organizations?

MATCH (ceo:Person)<-[:HAS_CEO]-(org:Organization)-[:HAS_INVESTOR]->(investedOrg:Organization)
WHERE (ceo)-[:HAS_INVESTOR]->(investedOrg)
RETURN org.name AS organization, ceo.name AS ceo, investedOrg.name AS investedOrganization
typeql: match $o isa organization, has name $n; limit 3; fetch { "org": $n };

question: List the organizations that have both a high revenue and a high number of employees.
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)
WHERE o.revenue IS NOT NULL AND o.nbrEmployees IS NOT NULL
  AND o.revenue > 1E8 AND o.nbrEmployees > 1000
RETURN o.name AS organization, o.revenue AS revenue, o.nbrEmployees AS employees
ORDER BY o.revenue DESC, o.nbrEmployees DESC
typeql: match $o isa organization, has name $n; limit 3; fetch { "org": $n };

question: Name the organizations with the most board members who are also CEOs of other organizations.

MATCH (o:Organization)<-[:HAS_BOARD_MEMBER]-(boardMember:Person)
WHERE EXISTS {
  (boardMember)-[:HAS_CEO]->(:Organization)
}
WITH o, count(boardMember) AS boardMemberCEOCount
RETURN o.name AS organization, boardMemberCEOCount
ORDER BY boardMemberCEOCount DESC
LIMIT 10
typeql: match $o isa organization, has name $n; limit 3; fetch { "org": $n };

question: List the top 5 cities by number of public organizations.

question: Which organizations are based in a country other than their CEO's nationality?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_CEO]->(ceo:Person),
      (o)-[:IN_CITY]->(:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(country:Country),
      (ceo)-[:HAS_PARENT*0..]->(parent:Person)
WHERE parent.name IS NOT NULL
  AND NOT EXISTS {
    (parent)-[:HAS_PARENT*0..]->(:Person)-[:HAS_CHILD*0..]->(ceoNationality:Person)
    WHERE (ceoNationality)-[:IN_CITY]->(:City)-[:IN_COUNTRY]->(country)
  }
RETURN o.name AS organization, ceo.name AS ceo, country.name AS country
typeql: match $o isa organization, has name $n; limit 3; fetch { "org": $n };

WHERE o.isPublic = true AND o.revenue > 100000000
RETURN o.name
typeql: match $o isa organization, has name $n; limit 3; fetch { "org": $n };

question: Name 3 organizations that are suppliers to 'New Energy Group'.
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization {name: 'New Energy Group'})<-[:HAS_SUPPLIER]-(supplier:Organization)
RETURN supplier.name
LIMIT 3
typeql: match $o isa organization, has name $n; limit 3; fetch { "org": $n };

question: Which cities are home to organizations with more than 300 employees?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:IN_CITY]->(c:City)
WHERE o.nbrEmployees > 300
RETURN c.name AS city
typeql: match $o isa organization, has name $n; limit 3; fetch { "org": $n };

question: Identify the top 5 articles with a positive sentiment greater than 0.8.
cypher:
MATCH (a:Article)
WHERE a.sentiment > 0.8
RETURN a.title, a.sentiment, a.siteName, a.date
ORDER BY a.sentiment DESC
LIMIT 5
typeql: match $o isa organization, has name $n; limit 3; fetch { "org": $n };

question: What are the names of the organizations that are subsidiaries of 'Accenture'?

MATCH (accenture:Organization {name: 'Accenture'})-[:HAS_SUBSIDIARY]->(subsidiary:Organization)
RETURN subsidiary.name
typeql: match $o isa organization, has name $n; (parent_org: $o, subsidiary_org: $s) isa subsidiary; $s has name $sn; limit 3; fetch { "parent": $n, "sub": $sn };

question: Name the children and parents of persons who are CEOs of organizations with more than 50 employees.

WHERE o.nbrEmployees > 50

OPTIONAL MATCH (p)-[:HAS_PARENT]->(parent:Person)
RETURN p.name AS ceo, collect(child.name) AS children, collect(parent.name) AS parents

question: List the top 5 cities with the most organizations in the 'Healthcare' industry.
cypher:
MATCH (c:City)<-[:IN_CITY]-(o:Organization)-[:HAS_CATEGORY]->(ic:IndustryCategory {name: 'Healthcare'})
WITH c, count(o) as orgCount
ORDER BY orgCount DESC
LIMIT 5
RETURN c.name as city, orgCount as numberOfHealthcareOrgs
typeql: match $o isa organization, has name $n; limit 3; fetch { "org": $n };

question: Which organizations have a motto related to 'security', list the top 3.
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)
WHERE o.motto CONTAINS 'security'
RETURN o.name AS organization, o.motto AS motto
ORDER BY o.name
LIMIT 3
typeql: match $o isa organization, has name $n; limit 3; fetch { "org": $n };

question: List the first 3 countries with organizations that have more than 100 employees.
cypher:
MATCH (c:Country)<-[:IN_COUNTRY]-(city:City)<-[:IN_CITY]-(o:Organization)
WHERE o.nbrEmployees > 100
RETURN c.name AS country, count(o) AS numOrganizations
ORDER BY numOrganizations DESC
LIMIT 3
typeql: match $o isa organization, has name $n; limit 3; fetch { "org": $n };

question: What are the top 3 articles mentioning 'New Energy Group'?
cypher:
MATCH (a:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(o:Organization {name: 'New Energy Group'})
RETURN a.title AS title, a.siteName AS siteName, a.date AS date
ORDER BY a.date DESC
LIMIT 3
typeql: match $a isa article, has title $t; (mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $o) isa mention; $o has name $n; limit 3; fetch { "title": $t, "org": $n };

question: List the top 5 organizations that are public and have a revenue less than 10 million.

WHERE o.isPublic = true AND o.revenue < 1E7

ORDER BY o.revenue DESC
LIMIT 5

question: List the organizations that have a sentiment score above 0.8 in their latest article mention.

question: What are the challenges faced by organizations headquartered in non-capital cities?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:IN_CITY]->(c:City)
WHERE c.name <> c.summary AND c.summary CONTAINS "capital"
WITH o, c
OPTIONAL MATCH (o)-[:HAS_CATEGORY]->(cat:IndustryCategory)
OPTIONAL MATCH (o)<-[:MENTIONS]-(a:Article)
RETURN o.name AS organization, o.summary AS org_summary, c.name AS city, 
       c.summary AS city_summary, cat.name AS industry, 
       a.title AS article_title, a.summary AS article_summary
ORDER BY o.name
typeql: match $a isa article, has title $t; (mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $o) isa mention; $o has name $n; limit 3; fetch { "title": $t, "org": $n };

WITH city, max(a.sentiment) AS maxSentiment
ORDER BY maxSentiment DESC
LIMIT 3
RETURN city.name AS cityName, maxSentiment
typeql: match $a isa article, has title $t; (mentioning_article: $a, mentioned_org: $o) isa mention; $o has name $n; limit 3; fetch { "title": $t, "org": $n };

question: Which organizations have a subsidiary in a city named 'Seattle'?
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_SUBSIDIARY]->(sub:Organization)-[:IN_CITY]->(c:City {name: 'Seattle'})
RETURN o.name AS organization, sub.name AS subsidiary
typeql: match $o isa organization, has name $n; (parent_org: $o, subsidiary_org: $s) isa subsidiary; $s has name $sn; limit 3; fetch { "parent": $n, "sub": $sn };

question: Identify the top 3 organizations with the most board members.

LIMIT 3
RETURN o.name AS organization, boardMemberCount

question: What are the names of the organizations that have a CEO named after a person with a summary mentioning 'CEO at Accenture'?
cypher:
MATCH (p:Person)
WHERE p.summary IS NOT NULL AND p.summary CONTAINS 'CEO at Accenture'
WITH p
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_CEO]->(ceo:Person)
WHERE ceo.name IS NOT NULL AND ceo.name = p.name
RETURN o.name AS organization
typeql: match $o isa organization, has name $n; limit 3; fetch { "org": $n };

question: List the first 5 organizations that have a board member with the same name as a CEO of another organization.
cypher:
MATCH (o1:Organization)-[:HAS_BOARD_MEMBER]->(p:Person),
      (o2:Organization)-[:HAS_CEO]->(p2:Person)
WHERE p.name = p2.name AND o1 <> o2
RETURN o1.name AS org_with_board_member, p.name AS person_name, o2.name AS org_with_same_name_ceo
LIMIT 5
typeql: match $o isa organization, has name $n; limit 3; fetch { "org": $n };

question: What are the names of the organizations that have a CEO with a name mentioned in an article with a sentiment score greater than 0.8?

      (article)-[:MENTIONS]->(org:Organization),
      (org)-[:HAS_CEO]->(ceo:Person)
WHERE article.sentiment > 0.8 AND ceo.name IS NOT NULL

question: Find the top 3 organizations that have the most board members who are also CEOs of other organizations.

ORDER BY ceo_board_members DESC
LIMIT 3

question: List the first 5 organizations that have a CEO with a name mentioned in at least two different articles and a revenue greater than 50 million.
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_CEO]->(ceo:Person)
WHERE o.revenue > 5e7
WITH o, ceo
MATCH (article1:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(ceo)
WITH o, ceo, count(article1) AS mentionCount
WHERE mentionCount >= 2
RETURN o.name AS organization, ceo.name AS ceo
LIMIT 5

question: Identify the top 3 organizations with the most subsidiaries headquartered in a city named 'Seattle'.

question: List the first 5 organizations that have a CEO with a name mentioned in more than one article and a revenue greater than 100 million.
cypher:
MATCH (o:Organization)-[:HAS_CEO]->(ceo:Person)
WHERE o.revenue > 1E8
WITH o, ceo
MATCH (article:Article)-[:MENTIONS]->(o)
WHERE article.title CONTAINS ceo.name
WITH o, ceo, count(article) AS mentionCount
WHERE mentionCount > 1
RETURN o.name AS organization, ceo.name AS ceo
LIMIT 5
